text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf
medium

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf

text:
the campaign — #letherspeak — aims to amend the laws so any survivor over the age of 18 can waive their right to anonymity if they so choose, without risking punishment to themselves or any media outlet which publishes their story with consent. 
in #tasmania and the #nt it is not legal for victims of sexual assault to ever share their story in the public sphere. effectively silencing their voices and ability to tell their stories and accounts. 
we are lobbying to change these laws. 
it would be great if #insta folks could sign the petition for change here: https://www.megaphone.org.au/petitions/let-her-speak?bucket=&source=twitter-share-button

#womensrights #humanrights #timesup #metoo #change

text:
facebook showed me this post from a year ago. it's now been two years since life changed forever. i'm simultaneously more fearful and more hopeful than ever.
.
.
at precisely this time a year ago, one of the darkest periods of my life began. as it became clear our country, including some of my closest friends and family, had elected a morally-repugnant, highly unqualified and volatile man to the presidency, i fell into a hole so deep i thought i would never find my way out again. my heart felt broken. i cried for days, fearing for the dark times i knew laid ahead for so many groups of people.
.
.
i'm not a religious person, but the sunday after the election, i found myself at a church whose minister takes social justice to a level i'd never seen among christians. while he himself was still reeling from the election results, he told those gathered that day to not lose hope. he reminded us that history's greatest periods of progress followed, indeed were catalyzed by, the darkest of times.
.
.
dred scott was a few years before lincoln’s election. .
.
the great depression preceded the new deal. .
.
progressive advances in the 60s and 70s came just after mccarthyism.
.
.
soon it became clear that, nightmarish and earth-shattering as this election & its aftermath have been, a sleeping giant was awakened on november 8, 2016. people have become more engaged in politics than i've ever seen in my lifetime, attending marches and rallies; donating money to organizations who would combat the fearful agenda put before us; finally, finally beginning to understand that we are not at the mercy of whoever is elected president. power doesn't just reside in the highest office in the land, but with us, the people. .
.
and here we are, one year later. still reeling, to be sure, but fighting like hell for what, i must periodically remind myself, the majority of our country knows to be right. and if the results of last night's elections tell us anything, with the election of people of color, women & lgbt politicians to positions previously only occupied by white men, it's that that sleeping giant isn't going to be lying down anytime soon.
.
.
#resist on, friends. happy anniversary.

text:
🙌🏿🙌🏾🙌🏽🙌🏼🙌🏻
.
today i sat down next to an older gentleman who was rocking his korean war veteran hat
.
seemingly different, we discovered that we are both writers
.
and we both ordered breakfast for lunch
.
he said it must be karmic
.
he asked me what type of writing i do. i said, lifestyle pieces, personal essays, and i’m writing my first book about motherhood
.
i asked him what he writes and he handed me a copy of his first book, just recently published, about germany in the 1930’s
.
he went on to say that the social events that led up to wwii are very similar to what is happening today in our current political landscape (🙄)
.
and then he said, ”but you want to know the difference? women!”
.
and i couldn’t have agreed more
.
he went on to say that women today have a right that we must exercise, because it can shift history repeating itself
.
amen
.
i’m so grateful for this hopeful, cosmic moment
.
and i am so encouraged and inspired by the women stepping up and speaking out, campaigning, and voting for all rights
.
i feel it in my bones that it’s time
.
women will change the world. we will move us forward and into a higher consciousness and way of being with one another
.
in a society that thrives off of women against women, i couldn’t be more proud of my sisterhood
.
i see you, women. let’s get it
.
✊🏻✊🏼✊🏽✊🏾✊🏿
.

text:
colabs conversations, hosted by the college of liberal arts & behavioral sciences and odei.

this is an important student forum, lead by a panel from the college, to discuss issues that affects students on campus. this particular conversation revolves around consent, accountability, and sexuality. this is in the wake of the #metoo and #timesup movements and the kavanuagh hearings...national issues and conversations that affect us right home!

wednesday, 11/14 at 11am-12pm and at 1pm-2pm in pab 114. (attend either session). snacks provided!

come join the conversation. your voice and experiences are important and need to be heard!
.
.
.

text:

.
each year the @willametteweek awards this special honor to young leaders working to make #portland a better place. no one is more deserving of this than christina.
.
for more than 8 years she has provided leadership in a variety of critical roles at @raphaelhousepdx. she now oversees our emergency shelter and housing programs, guiding a team of 21 advocates and ensuring that families we serve receive the best possible support.
.
a survivor herself, christina advocates tirelessly for all those in our programs, and her accolades are many. .
click the link in our bio to read more, and show your support for her and all our work at #raphaelhouse!

text_retweet:
spark it up snoop!
•
#repost @sirpennypacker
• • • • •
😅 #savage #howitsdone #fucktrump — @snoopdogg has always been a character. we've loved him for years as he's turned into the uncle we all wish we had.
-
at times, he's funny. at others, he can spit some real talk. sometimes, he combines the two to send a message. tuesday's midterm elections were a major story in the united states with many artists urging their fans to get out and vote.
-
#donaldtrump has been critiqued heavily for his unconventional tactics as trump and snoop has been a major source of scrutiny. he decided to make his way to the white house to leave his mark, lighting up a blunt as he observed the secret service from afar.
-
the rapper can be seen saying in one clip posted on instagram that while other americans were "doing all this other bullshit" amid the midterm elections, he decided to temporarily camp out nearby the white house to smoke, saying: "f--- the president."
-
#snoop dogg could be seen in other clips walking throughout what appears to be lafayette park while talking to fans with his blunt in hand, making his way over to a few benches.
-
of course, he documented the entire process as his instagram is filled with videos of him doing his thing. along the way, he took some photos with fans and even complimented an elderly man on his hair.
-
the west coast legend was excited about his visit, going a little overboard with posts from the president's home.
-
he has been critical of trump in the past. now, he's fine sparking up in front of his house to send a message. in his words, he just "had 2 do it."
—
"i don't give a f---. i tell 'em straight up, motherf---er. if you like that n---a, you motherf---in' racist," snoop dogg said in the interview, condemning supporters of #trump, including west. "f--- you and f--- him. now what?"
-
at the time, snoop dogg also said that he feels trump supporters are condoning racism.
-
snoop dogg also drew criticism from trump supporters last year after he shot a clown dressed as trump with a toy gun in one of his music video.
—

text:
när själen värker och man klarar inte av att ens se inslaget från #uppdraggranskning utan måste se det i två etapper för att ens orka ta in. ———————————————————————— för jag vet att hon inte är ensam och jag vet att systemet är uppbyggt för att inte vara till för den vårdsökande och framförallt inte för den vårdkrävande. och alla som arbetar inom vården, har en svårt sjuk vän el anhörig vet att det är just så. för om du är svårt sjuk, med flera diagnoser gör sjukhuset, avdelning, mottagningen rätt i att skicka dig vidare, neka dig vård osv. för om du har ett missbruk, nej då kan vi inte behandla din anorexia det går emot deras policy och har du anorexia näh då finns inte resurser på beroendecentrum, och har du varit med om trauman näh då ska du till en psykolog, o har du självskadat ja då ska du till psykakuten men där får du bara akut behandling och sedan måste du vidare o så fortsätter det... ———————————————————————— för det sjukvårdssystem vi har, oavsett kunskap, mediciner och medicintekniskutrustning så är systemet inte gjort för att funka. och du är aldrig så ensam som när du är sjuk och vårdsökande. 
men välkomnas med varm hand om du i princip är frisk och ditt besök tar inte mer än 20min. ja då finns oändliga alternativ och vårdformer för just dig. du har en läkare i mobilen om du så önskar. #räddasanne @svt  @uppdraggranskning #svensksjukvård #allamänniskorslikavärde #psykiskohälsa #vårdpersonal #vemkanräddasanne #utanskyddsnät #intedinhora #metoo #vårdkris

text:
“while in the midst of serious internal growth respect your need to rest” @yung_pueblo -
i pulled up to my fav little coffee shop today to get some work done and my body whispered “nooooo”.
-
i took a minute to slow down and listen to that loud whisper. decided to go home instead. two naps. nourishing lunch and dinner. in bed early tonight reading. and today, this is healing 🙏🏼💚

text:
have i told you how much i absolutely adore my job? not just for the #travel perks or the fact that i get to work with some of the most interesting people on the planet, but because every single day feels new and b’c i realize how incredibly #lucky i am to have found precisely what i was intended for. as an #advertising creative director, my job title doesn’t sound as #honorable as some others, but over my career, i’m #proud to say i’ve created work to help return abducted children to their homes, bring farmers in the heartland the sort of choices that won’t cost them their farms and save the lives of over 160k shelter pets... and counting. i’ve had a hand in growing businesses that people—from baristas to indie bike dealers to immigrant ceo’s—count on. and that’s not nothing.

i *absolutely* adore this job and recognize how lucky i’ve been, especially in this last year, when i was having to pull myself through the death-throes of a physically-abusive relationship. not everyone gets this kind of blessing. in fact, according to a 2004 report from the world health organization, up to 60% of victims of intimate partner violence lose their jobs as a result of the abuse.

i can only imagine how low i’d feel if, in addition to my safety and peace and self-esteem, my ex had cost me my career. but the awareness of this—knowing it happens, seeing it happen to other women in my periphery—gives me #perspective and fire, both for the workplace i drive up to each day and for the work that needs to be done for #abusevictims. as soon as i’m back from this #businesstrip, imma figure out how to chip away at that terrible stat. please let me know if you want to join me; i hope a few of you will, b’c, as with everything else, together, #wegotthis.
.
.
.
#thegirlwholeftthenarc #breakthesilence #nomoreabuse #dvsurvivor #recoveryqueen #womensupportingwomen #antibullying #dvfacts #dv101 #narcissistsurvivorgroup  #alignment #personalgrowth #agencylife #workworkwork #thehappynow #selflovejourney #metoo #sundog  #gratefulheart #tribevibes #sosheslays

repost via @instarepost20 from @bruce_wayne11 jupiter in scorpio♏ this time around brought on  #metoo and accolades to tonya harding's life story on the big screen...including the oscar for best supporting actress. harding was born with jupiter in scorpio♏, so in fact all the attention is  credited to her jupiter return. 
written october 9, 2017
jupiter in scorpio

in 1994 at the us figuring skating championships...1 month before the winter olympics, nancy kerrigan was brutally clubbed leaving her unable to compete.  her rival, tonya harding, swore up and down she had nothing to do with it, but the truth was revealed.  it was discovered that her ex husband and bodyguard conspired to attack kerrigan.  harding was later convicted and given 3 years probation, 500 hours of community service,  160,000 dollar fine...and banned from the us figuring skating association for life.  this was big headlines that year, and yes jupiter was transiting scorpio♏. it will be interesting to see what's uncovered this time.  #realastrologywayne #astrology #nancykerrigan #tonyaharding #jupiterinscorpio

text:
💰ну что, самое интересное - бюджет трипа по сша на арендном байке😏
(без учета билетов дотуда)
.
🔻самая большая статья расходов - аренда байка. здесь сложно что-то найти дешевле 100$ в день. к ценам обычно ещё добавляется налог и страховка. самая дешевая ямаха wr, которую я присмотрела, стоит 140-160$. однако владельцу нужно было перегнать ее в аризону, и с условием перегона цена сократилась до 70$. со страховкой и всем остальным я отдала за байк в районе 690$. нужно ещё было оставить немалый залог, но его целиком вернули обратно. было бы больше денег на залог- цена страховки была бы меньше.
.
🔻жильё. я ночевала 2 раза в палатке в лесу, 1 раз в кемпинге (35$), три раза в мотелях (65$x3) и один раз по каучсерфингу. если бы не дубак, мотелей в списке бы не было) хостелы есть только в больших городах, и то не во всех.
.
🔻еда. где-то 80$ у меня ушло на еду и горелку, газ, посуду и каремат. и ещё на 60 я несколько раз поела в различных забегаловках.
.
🔻бензин. на топливо ушли смешные 75$. литр стоит меньше доллара и это прекрасно!
.
🔻входные билеты. я планировала купить абонемент в нац.парки за 80$, но не успела - и хорошо! во всех парках, где я была, или был бесплатный вход (несезон), или я проезжала их кусочки дебрями бесплатно. 30$ за тур по шахте в колорадо.
.
♦️итого: 690+230+70+140+30=1160 за недельный трип. а, еще на 15$ я себе купила у индейцев ожерелье на память. все!
.
♦️вывод: в штатах дорого, да. многие вещи дороже чем у нас. при определённом уровне автономности деньги можно почти не тратить, например в один день я потратила только 10$ на бензин и хот-дог на заправке, остальное готовила сама. но так как это отпуск, пару раз таки побаловала себя хорошим стейком и тёплой кроватью. ведь таки удовольствие от жизни нужно не забывать получать!
.
🇺🇸budget of my 7-day off-road trip from denver to phoenix amounted to $1160. is is a lot or not for the states?
.
👉that included: bike rental for a week, food, lodging (2*nights in tent for free, 1 camping, 1 couchsurfing, 3*motels because it was so cold), buying some camping equipment and gas; that’s everything i needed. luckily no repairs, could’ve been much more!
.
#4dearlife_transporter #мотопутешествие

text_retweet:
#repost @ibelievethem ・・・
#repost (thanks for the tag!) @rapesurvivorsupport
・・・
i call those affected by sexual violence "survivors." i have spent the better part of a year waiting to feel some magical transition from "victim" to "survivor," as if one day i would conquer the key to stopping all of the immeasureable pain havoc wreaked on my life. truthfully, i have yet to feel like a survivor. on most days, i feel robbed and like i am grieving for a version of myself that i am not sure exists anymore. but more importantly, every victim/survivor deserved the right to claim whatever term makes then feel the most comfortable or more accurately represents their feelings.

secondly, we must use our language intentionally. something bad did not happen to me. someone did something bad to me. that someone raped me. it was not an accident, it was not "something bad, it was rape.
it is up to us to frame our trauma because unfortunately the rest of the world will not do it for us, or will do so with victim blaming and stigma. 
#ibelievethem .
.

i call those affected by sexual violence "survivors." i have spent the better part of a year waiting to feel some magical transition from "victim" to "survivor," as if one day i would conquer the key to stopping all of the immeasureable pain havoc wreaked on my life. truthfully, i have yet to feel like a survivor. on most days, i feel robbed and like i am grieving for a version of myself that i am not sure exists anymore. but more importantly, every victim/survivor deserved the right to claim whatever term makes then feel the most comfortable or more accurately represents their feelings.

secondly, we must use our language intentionally. something bad did not happen to me. someone did something bad to me. that someone raped me. it was not an accident, it was not "something bad, it was rape.
it is up to us to frame our trauma because unfortunately the rest of the world will not do it for us, or will do so with victim blaming and stigma. 
#ibelievethem .
.

text:
as brendan o’neill puts it, defamation cases are ‘obnoxious’ and illiberal. i love this article by jia tolentino - women are being threatened and stifled by enraged men who have abused them, who attack them again and again when they dare to speak up and sound a warning for others. misusing the law to attempt to silence them is immoral, evil and cowardly. my own attacker has done this very thing - a letter from his lawyer threatening me with court action for daring to expose his crime to the world. and people wonder why sexual assault victims are too afraid to speak up? this is why! this is abuse of power, intimidation of victims and a sad reflection of the society we live in that sides with criminals and abusers over victims

text_retweet:
#repost @sirpennypacker
• • • • •
😅 #savage #howitsdone #fucktrump — @snoopdogg has always been a character. we've loved him for years as he's turned into the uncle we all wish we had.
-
at times, he's funny. at others, he can spit some real talk. sometimes, he combines the two to send a message. tuesday's midterm elections were a major story in the united states with many artists urging their fans to get out and vote.
-
#donaldtrump has been critiqued heavily for his unconventional tactics as trump and snoop has been a major source of scrutiny. he decided to make his way to the white house to leave his mark, lighting up a blunt as he observed the secret service from afar.
-
the rapper can be seen saying in one clip posted on instagram that while other americans were "doing all this other bullshit" amid the midterm elections, he decided to temporarily camp out nearby the white house to smoke, saying: "f--- the president."
-
#snoop dogg could be seen in other clips walking throughout what appears to be lafayette park while talking to fans with his blunt in hand, making his way over to a few benches.
-
of course, he documented the entire process as his instagram is filled with videos of him doing his thing. along the way, he took some photos with fans and even complimented an elderly man on his hair.
-

text:
wie oft wird unter frauen/mädchen die gleiche bullshit-story erzählt? nicht nein sagen zu können, um den typen nicht emotional zu verletzen. nein zu sagen, es trotzdem hinzunehmen und sich selbst dafür zu verurteilen. so etwas wie loyalität gegenüber dem täter zu verspüren und scham davor, verurteilt und ausgestoßen zu werden oder angst, als lügnerin dazustehen! .
.
es ist so unglaublich wichtig, kindern wirklich mal zuzuhören, sie wahrzunehmen, den rahmen zu halten und ihnen mit liebe zu begegnen, das besondere in ihnen zu stärken und halt zu geben. 
um wirklich einen unterschied im leben eines anderen zu machen, reichen oftmals ein paar stunden unserer zeit... .
.großes lob an ein junges mädchen, das ich gestern kennenlernen durfte und das den mut bewies und sich mir anvertraute. ich empfinde großen dank für ihr vertrauen. und ich bin ...wütend darüber, dass sie vergewaltigt wurde. ...tief entsetzt, dass sie sich selbst die schuld gibt. (sie ist ja freiwillig zu ihm gegangen!) ...schockiert, dass sie sich schämt und es still erträgt. ...traurig, dass ich nicht mehr tun kann. .
.

text:
working from the road today!

all week we’ve been planning for a sneak peek into our business- today i shared my story of how my life had transformed over the past 4.5 years- how i was an exhausted over worked momma who was desperate for time with my family- and unexpectedly found it with an online business.... sharing my story is my way of giving back- so many people don’t realize there are  opportunities that can give you a completely different life! 
so, yesterday when my girlfriend text me for a spontaneous road trip- i didn’t even hesitate to say yes- cause my office is mobile if i need it to be! today, as i spoke my truth with the intention to inspire- my baby girl sat in the back seat- she will grow up knowing how i’ve been able to be with her every day since i walked away from my full time job when she was 7 months old.

this is the type of freedom i craved- and work so dang hard for.... better to die fighting for freedom then be a prisoner all the days of your life!

text:
after feeling outraged about @cerclecheung’s post on how she was sexually assaulted by a local photographer she hired during a photoshoot here in nyc. i've decided to write a little guide to women who are about to partake & meet a photographer for the first time.
-
1. check references, ask his past clients what their experience was.
2. meet in a safe location, do not go to his house or to a secluded area
3. if you agree on a nude or sexy shoot, you have the right to bring an escort, (boyfriend, sister friend etc) i always encourage people to bring someone if my wife isn't able to come along and help. if he insists on you coming alone that's a sign that you shouldn’t go alone.
4. if he persists on nudes; don't do it!
5. go with your gut feeling! your gut never lies!
6. if you are sexually assaulted report it to authorities asap. it is not your fault!
-
guys like this, make professionals like me look bad and on behalf of all professional photographers out there, i'd like to apologize to everyone who has been sexually assaulted by their photographer. safety has always been the utmost importance to me, both for me and the models i work with, and if i ever made anyone feel uncomfortable, unsafe or have said anything inappropriate; i'm sorry!!
-
this post goes out to the real warriors out there who are brave enough to come forward after they were assaulted.  you're the real warriors! 💪🏼
-
i’m offering the young lady (@cerclecheung) a free shoot when she feels comfortable and ready to work with another photographer!
-
🧘🏽‍♀️ @yvettejain (model is not the victim in the assault) 🧘🏽‍♀️
#yoga #integrity #real #metoo #ibelieveher #yonyc

text:
this friday, nov. 9, at 8 p.m., hawaiʻi playbuilders will debut its “#metoo survivors’ circle” at the  arts at marks garage. the play will feature community members who have come forward to share their own sexual harassment experiences, as well as professional actors telling real stories. the initiative aims to give sequence to a project that began at @hawaiipacificuniversity under the title “#metoo monologues,” produced by hpu graduate student maysa thayer in april. “#metoo survivors’ circle” will have six performances over two weeks in november. for this season, madden was contemplating adding a discussion panel at end of the performance, but as of this week, it hasn’t been confirmed. tickets are available at eventbrite.

text_retweet:
repost @laviaminora 
dear agni,
.
kamu tidak sendiri. saya juga penyintas.
di usia 4 tahun, saya dicabuli oleh sepupu sendiri.
tapi saya diam, sebab saya tidak tahu apa yang dia lakukan.
.
kamu tidak sendiri. saya juga korban.
di usia 10 tahun, seorang tukang becak menyekap saya di lorong sekolah, dan menjamah liang senggama saya.
saya cuma mingkem, sebab saya takut dianggap tidak bisa jaga diri.
.
kamu tidak sendiri. saya pernah dilecehkan.
di usia 17 tahun, saya bersepeda di jalanan sepi sambil memakai celana training dan hoodie. tiba-tiba seorang bapak menepuk pantat saya.
saya terdiam, karena ketakutan dan tidak bisa bereaksi apa-apa.
.
dear agni,
.
saya tahu rasanya, karena #sayajuga mengalaminya. mau melawan, tapi merasa tidak berdaya. mau mengadu, tapi takut dibikin malu. mau marah-marah sambil membanting, tapi orang tidak pernah menganggap ini penting.
.
sekarang karenamu, keberanian ini bertunas, agni!
suaramu melengking, memekakkan telinga, menerobos batas-batas timpangnya keadilan. sumbu telah ditarik, dan terimakasih atas api yang kau pantik.
.
mulai hari ini dan seterusnya, kita kawal bersama rasa amanmu, rasa aman para wanita yang masih bersembunyi di balik besar dan kuatnya rasa takut. bukan saatnya untuk kita merasa lemah.
.
dan terima kasih paling besar buatmu karena telah menyadarkan bahwa kita bukan barang yang bisa disejajarkan dengan jamahan!
.
untuk semua wanita yang mengalami hal yang sama, kita adalah agni, dan kita adalah api!

#kitaagni
#metoo 
#sayajuga 
#kamibersamaagni ---
these picts are taken and directed by a beautiful soul: @bamzery ❤️

text:
#feminism #taranaburke and #metoo.
tarana burke (born september 12, 1973) is an african-american civil rights activist from the bronx, new york who founded the me too movement. in 2006, burke began using the phrase "me too" to raise awareness of the pervasiveness of sexual abuse and assault in society, and the phrase developed into a broader movement, following the 2017 use of #metoo as a hashtag following the harvey weinstein sexual abuse allegations. time named burke, among a group of other prominent activists dubbed "the silence breakers", as the time person of the year for 2017. burke attends public speaking events across the country and is currently senior director at girls for gender equity.
source: @wikipedia

text:
to some, it's just a bottle. to me, it's a reminder and memento of an epic moment - my book release party. this was a bottle i specially chose to celebrate a special moment in my life. when i look at it, i think about how far i'd come to even have arrived to that point in my life, and i remember those who were there for me (in spirit and in person) at that celebration. it's also a reminder of all the lives i've touched since releasing the book. in this week where progress for women has been made across the country with all of us collectively using our voices to make change, this bottle reminds me to take a breath and congratulate and say cheers to us all for moving forward - every day, one step at a time. and a special thank you, as always, to the one and only epic stephanie, lead cocktail server / bottle service at the high end lounge rose room, who is also our friend and takes such exceptional care of us (for this special event, and every time). 👌🏽

text:
oyuncu pamela anderson, hollywood’daki taciz olaylarının konuşulması için başlatılan #metoo hareketini aşırı bulduğunu açıkladı.
 yıllar önce yayınlanan 'sahil güvenlik' dizisiyle ünlenen oyuncu pamela anderson, günümüz feminist hareketiyle ilgili konuştu. 51 yaşındaki kanadalı oyuncu katıldığı bir televizyon programında, “bence feminizm çok ileri gidiyor olabilir" dedi ve ekledi: "ben bir feministim ama bence üçüncü dalga feminizm bunaltıcı. bana göre erkekleri felce uğratıyor. #metoo hareketi bana biraz aşırı geliyor. üzgünüm, bunu söylediğim için öldürülebilirim.” anderson, hollywood’un ünlü yapımcısı harvey weinstein’in, aralarında ünlü oyuncuların da bulunduğu pek çok kadını, kariyeriyle tehdit ederek taciz etmesiyle ilgili de konuştu. ünlü oyuncu, “annem bana şunu öğretti: bir yabancıyla otele gitme. eğer biri kapıyı bornozla açıyorsa ve bu bir iş görüşmesiyse, belki de bir başkasıyla birlikte katılmalıyım. bence bu tarz şeyler sadece sağduyuyla alakalı. ya da içeri gir ve işi al” dedi.  arkadaşlarınızı etiketleyin onların da haberi olsun#magazin #haber

text:
the time i got me back...
.
.
getting ready to record this one.  i wrote this song about myself.  it’s called “my friend”. it’s about a time when i felt like i lost myself.  there was a time i got so busy trying to please others...got so occupied with trying to be all things to all people, and tried so hard to act like i had everything together when in truth...i didn’t.  i lost me.  this song was my way of getting me back.
.
.
the lyrics go “i wanna love you. and it feels so good to hear your voice again and i love to have you back my friend.” sometimes the only connection you need is reconnection with yourself.  sometimes the only love you need is the love you can give yourself.  and sometimes you gotta miss you so much that you’re willing to fight to get you back.  isn’t that a fight worth fighting for? love you.  like you. reclaim you ✊🏾💜
.
.
✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨✨

.

.

text:
where are you in your process of change? it’s a good question to ask yourself throughout you journey in life, especially when you choose to live a life of growth and self love. this is a necessary path for abuse survivors. you see, it catches up with you - the secrets, the darkness, the fears. they lurk. they fester. .
.
.
so choose to build your cocoon. your nice, strong, safe cocoon woven with love for you and your future. know that the work you do on yourself as you develop into the most beautiful version of you is going to be painful at times. it’s challenging and arduous. it’s good though. the challenges make you resilient as your bold colors fill in. and when you’re ready, emergence is slow. be gentle with yourself. give yourself the time you need to unfold and fly. .
.
.
your life is a blessing. your cocoon of healing is a powerful process as a lightning woman. your power is choice. your power is love. one day you will fly free. you’re precious. know that. it’s all worth the wait. 🐛🦋
.
.
.

text: my experience as a new mom shook my world. it broke me and made the new me all at once. i am a planner and a control freak so i thought i had everything under control. little did i know i had to leave that control up to my family because i could do nothing but rest. i meal prepped and i thought this was enough. after a weeks rest i did some laundry and got out of my sweat pants.  this made my usually low blood pressure rocket sky high and my midwife warned me medication was a last resort. relaxation and recuperation was my priority.  i have learned so much going through this experience and i am going to help revolutionize the postpartum care period because moms deserve better. i went into this pregnancy the healthiest i've ever been! so i feel for the ladies who have body issues going into pregnancy. its hard enough as it is! my goal is to inspire you to plan your postpartum recovery and have all the support in the right places for you! not just for your baby. dm me for more on this topic or tune into my podcast coming soon. #postpartum #postpartumrevolution #holisticmamma #momsdeservebetter #birth #bethebestmomyoucanbe #momsfirst

text:
when we educate about sexual health and sexual violence, it can bring up "stuff" for a lot of folks, which can lead to discomfort (we don't mean trauma, just to be clear). sometimes, the discomfort is thrown back onto the messenger for delivering the message that the recipient finds uncomfortable. other times, the recipient tries to shut down the messenger, believing that everyone around them is also feeling uncomfortable. and on some occasions, the messenger is told that these conversations are wrong to have. we acknowledge that talking about sexual health and violence isn't easy because it requires us to do our own work. however, we cannot change what's happening around us without first addressing what's happening within. [image description: black text on a white background with the words "never have i dealt with anything more difficult than my own soul" by imam al-ghazali]

#sexeducation #metoo #metoomovement #justice #healing

text: 🚨 the inferior pin is here 🚨 angela saini’s book ‘inferior: how science got women wrong and the new research that’s rewriting the story’ took the world by storm when it was released last year. with the continuation of the #metoo movement, the #trump administration and all the rest of the shit things going on in the world, this book gave us #feminists hope. these soft enamel pins are now up for sale in the @scienceonapostcard shop, and a percentage of profits from sales will be donated to @refugecharity. refuge provides a range of life-saving and life-changing services to empower women and children to rebuild their lives after domestic violence. we are so happy to be supporting @refugecharity with this pin release ♥️

text:
if you’re an hr professional or manager looking for practical advice about workplace harassment, discrimination and bullying that you can implement straightaway, attend a tell jane seminar.
whether attending a webinar from the comfort of your desk or coming along to a breakfast briefing, you’ll come away equipped with an increased understanding and top tips that you can implement that very day – indeed, striking while the iron is hot is very much at the heart of these seminars.
as hr professionals, we’re often expected to deal with the aftermath of a harassment case, but how do we get on the front foot and prevent it happening in the first place? prevention is better than cure, and this is very much our ethos. link in bio for more information 
#hr #humanresources #seminar #breakfast #london #reading #metoo #timesup #harassment #womeninbusiness #smallbusiness #businessowner

text:
estreamos hoje no teatro da trindade!

canção do bandido | ópera
teatro da trindade | 8 a 18 de novembro
qua 19h | qui e sáb 21h | dom 16h30

música & direcção musical nuno côrte-real
libreto pedro mexia
encenação ricardo neves-neves

cantores andré henriques, bárbara barradas, cátia moreso, inês simões, marco alves dos santos e sónia alcobaça
coro do teatro nacional de são carlos e orquestra sinfónica portuguesa

cenário henrique ralheta
figurinos rafaela mapril 
desenho de luz luís duarte 
assistência de encenação rafael gomes e diana vaz

produção executiva força de produção
coprodução teatro da trindade inatel, teatro nacional de são carlos e temporada darcos

partindo do conto tradicional o macaco de rabo cortado, canção do bandido imagina uma personagem que não é um macaco mas um advogado, casanova dos tempos modernos, homem que acumula conquistas e as vai trocando por novas conquistas, sem pensar muito nas consequências dos seus atos. 
o casanovismo e o donjuanismo são revisitados numa época em que as guerras dos sexos (ou dos géneros) já não são o que eram, ou têm pelo menos discursos e legitimidades diferentes. coros gregos e essencialismos em tempos digitais e de #metoo? em quem devemos acreditar: no libreto, nos protagonistas, nos antagonistas, ou nas personagens que, falando em vez de cantar, contestam estes diálogos, estes tipos, esta dialética? 
de d. giovanni à música pop, dos bordões linguísticos aos jogos nonsense, as personagens de «canção do bandido» trazem para o palco tudo o que lhes ocorre, tudo o que sirva as suas estratégias ou ilustra as suas dúvidas. e os espectadores, certamente, tomam partido.

classificação etária | m12

bilheteira

tel: 213 420 000 
e-mail: bilheteira.trindade@inatel.pt

horário
terça a sábado: 14:00 às 20:00
domingo: 14:00 às 18:00
dias de espetáculo até 30 minutos após o início
segunda: encerrada 
bilheteira online 
https://teatrodatrindade-inatel.bol.pt

text:
in honor of all the ladies who were elected to congress on tuesday, i’d like to give a shout out to the incredibly empowering ladies that have mentored and inspired me on this here path of mine:
🙌🏼marie, you make me more confident in following my path even when it doesn’t quite look like what other people are doing
💪🏼shalene, you show me how to persevere both in the pursuit of self and career in the face of patriarchal roadblocks
🤟🏼alice, you show me how to keep my heart open and to help others even when life gets hard
✊🏼grandma fern, your bravery to stand up to grandpa on behalf of your autonomy despite all you were up against is a source of power for me daily
❤️
i work with a lot of young women and hope to someday be able to lift them up as much as y’all have me 😍

text:
a las justicia no le importa que cada 20 horas muera una mujer por violencia machista, no importa cuantas denuncias hagamos, no importa que tan lastimadas física y psicológicamente nos deje un marido/novio, ó ex, no nos creerán hasta ver nuestra carne en estado de descomposición abandonado en una bolsa de residuos en algún baldío descampado. y si osamos defemendernos somos estigmatizadas, demonizadas, como pasó con nahir galarza. si nos defendemos y matamos en legitima  defenza para la justicia machista, nosotras siempre seremos culpables y condenadas.

no se puede cambiar esta matanza y violencia diaria que sufrimos mujeres y niñas hasta que cambie la justicia y haya una política especifica de defensa hacia las mujeres.

#feminismo #niunamenos #metoo #powergirl #justicia #strong #feminist #respet #injusticia #machismo #sexismo #nomas #violenciadegenero #stop #nomore #violenciainstitucional #patriarcado #justiciamachista #misoginia #radicalfeminist #radfem

text:
today, i gave a presentation on the importance of designing technical and organizational systems to fit our human capabilities and limitations. 
the audience consisted of about 70 people working in tank shipping. 
i concluded my talk by taking the opportunity to talk about #metoo and the narratives shared by 1100 swedish women seafarers. 
not everybody are comfortable listening to these stories. but they need to be told.

one year after, i had hoped that we would see more progress. but it is evident that we need to continue talking about our social work environment and remind ourselves and all decision makers out there of a part of reality as ugly as dickpics.

has this never happened to you?
are you not affected, personally?
great!! then you can still make a change by not being a passive bystander. 
use the powerful voice you have for those without a platform. 
rock the boat.

#wista #wistasweden 
#womeninshipping 
#womenwhomovestheworld 
#metoo 
#lättaankar #anchorsaweigh 
#maritimesafety

text:
jak powinna wyglądać skrzywdzona osoba, żebyś jej uwierzył?
może wyrażać emocje po ujawnieniu przemocy i nie słyszeć, że to podważa jej wiarygodność? może nie chcieć być oskarżana o kłamstwo przez obcych ludzi na podstawie zdjęć, które wrzuca? może po prostu nie obchodzić jej przydługie zdanie w jej sprawie tego pana, tamtego pana, a nawet wczesnego i późnego wittgensteina?

what should the victim look like to be believed?
can she speak about her emotions after speaking up? can she not be silenced by the unjustified accusation of making false testimony? can she just not care what this guy, that guy and even early and young wittgenstein think about her case?

text:
я потянула сухожилие левой ноги

и да, я не нашла ничего лучше, с чего можно было бы начать. я на протяжении большого количества времени не занималась ни активизмом, ни инстаграмом, ни своим здоровьем, что дало о себе знать

мне очень приятно, что некоторые люди были искренне рады моему возвращению (спасибо за поддержку 🖤) и мне было интересно снова поддерживать с вами дискуссии, но:

скорее всего эта страница уйдет в прошлое и останется там, как хорошие и забытые воспоминания из жизни. и с этим ничего не поделать

мое время занято с самого утра и до следующего утра в прямом смысле, я усердно учусь (ну или пытаюсь), хотя это тоже не сплошные радости и, как вы уже могли догадаться, я максимум успеваю загрузить пару историй

и как бы мне ни хотелось ещё и вести инстаграм, это реально большой труд

возможно, кому-то это покажется смешно, но быть онлайн 24/7, искать аудиторию, делать контент, радоваться жизни и привлекать публику чем-то сверхновым реально сложно и требует времени и внимания

иногда я буду появляться (а может быть и опять начну свою деятельность), а пока до новых встреч

с любовью,
карина
name: ♡Karina♡柯瑞哪♡

text:
em diversos países já é comemorado o dia da igualdade salarial, o que ainda não inclui o brasil. um dos melhores exemplos de campanhas em prol dessa batalha vem da inglaterra, onde a política stella creasy junto de parlamentares mulheres acaba de criar a campanha #paymetoo, espécie de desdobramento do tão falado movimento “#metoo”, que luta contra o assédio sexual em ambiente de trabalho.
estudo feito pela organização internacional do trabalho divulgado no dia internacional da mulher, 8 de março de 2018, mostrou que ainda estamos longe de um cenário ideal. se mantermos o ritmo atual serão necessários 70 anos para acabar com a diferença de salário entre os sexos. o japão, por exemplo, é o país com menos mulheres em cargos de chefia – apenas 7%. já no brasil, mulheres ainda ganham 22% a menos que os homens, taxa que, dependendo da profissão, pode chegar a 40%.
a constituição federal consagra o princípio da isonomia em seu artigo 5° caput, onde diz que “todos são iguais perante a lei, sem distinção de qualquer natureza”, inclusive de gênero, sendo assim a luta contra a discriminação, tendo em vista a distinção salarial entre homens e mulheres, deve continuar!

#igualdadesalarial #igualdadedegêneros #direitodeigualdade #princípiodaigualdade #direitoconstitucional #direito #isonomia #advocaciasilvaesilva #informação #advogadas_em_ação #igualdadedireitodetodos #lutacontraadescriminação
name: Advocacia Silva e Silva

text:
it’s astonishing that there are yogis that believe in reincarnation across lives, yet they can’t see the impact of enslaved or otherwise subjugated ancestors on modern people of color. 🖤 they can’t connect generations of societal prejudice against lgbt people, to our tendency towards self destructive behaviors. gay men are 3 times more like to use drugs. lesbian teens are 5 times more likely to attempt suicide. 🖤 in yoga philosophy, we talk about samskaras, which are powerful psychological imprints. everything leaves them, every action or intention. maybe they can travel through time. maybe they can run in families. it is our yogic duty to see these seeds and counteract them. it’s my yogic duty to help you with yours when possible. i believe this kind of justice is the light shining on my yogic path. what do you think? can karma work in this way? are samskaras deeply personal work? or can we each be a light too, might we help each other see? •
•
#existgently #ashtangachallenge #yogalife #yogainspiration #socialjustice #blacklivesmatter #metoo #transisbeautifull #itsallconnected

text:
today jupiter moves out of deep, dark, transformative scorpio and into curious, adventurous, thought-provoking, and expansive sagittarius until december 2, 2019. this is a big shift that is going to bring about some big changes. ⠀
⠀
jupiter is the ruler of sagittarius so this move is like coming home. jupiter feels most like itself now and can express its energy in the purest and most natural way. sagittarius immediately follows scorpio, the sign of death, transformation, and shadow. scorpio clears out the baggage that weighs us down and holds us back. this gives sagittarius the freedom it needs to fly off to new lands and explore new ideas. ⠀
⠀
with jupiter in sagittarius, you will be introduced to infinite possibilities and opportunities. jupiter is considered the lucky planet so don't be surprised if you just so happen to stumble into your life purpose over the next 12 months or get a once in a lifetime opportunity. overall, the energy of the world will be much lighter and optimistic. new conversations will be had and a desire to understand other ways of life will begin to develop. the next 12 months is all about exploration. how can i see things with fresh, new eyes?⠀
⠀
sagittarius is the sign of philosophy so take advantage of anything that allows you to learn something new or better yet, to create your own methods of teaching and sharing information. now is an excellent time to introduce your views to the world. jupiter and sagittarius rule publishing, higher education, broadcasting, and enterprising so finding a platform to voice your opinion will be easier than ever. now is an excellent time to write a book or program, start a business (especially in communication and travel), to go back to school, or to take a siesta and travel for a bit. ⠀
⠀
finally, jupiter always brings some issue to light. jupiter in scorpio brought us the #metoo movement which started within days of this transit. immigration has been a hot topic over recent months and is likely to become an even bigger issue now. don't be surprised if we see some major immigration overhauls. ⠀
⠀
enjoying these astrology posts? be sure to let me know by commenting below. #astrology #spiritelement ⠀

text:
yesterday i had the opportunity to talk about parker handbags from the perspective of wellness and selfcare and in light of amazing new things coming, i want to say thank you to every one out there doing big things for women and so many thank yous to everyone who has supported parker handbags. 
my journey started with developing a handbag for off body carry that made me feel confident to walk to my car alone, in the dark, after work. 
after realizing that my concern is shared by women everywhere, i have shifted the focus of parker handbags to work toward creating a system that empowers women to actively rewrite the script around sexual harassment and assault, regardless of what they choose to carry. 
all in all, i want to provide woman a way to care for their safety and wellbeing in every situation, in a way that makes them feel beautiful, confident and safe.

the big dream. a hard end to gender based violence because enough is enough. 
#parkerhandbags #stopsexualassault #staysafebeauty #metoo #timesup #functionalfashion #enoughisenough #theperfecthandbag #thefutureisfemale #womanboss #loveyourselfenoughtoprotectyourself

text:
la segunda y última jornada del #congresovg18 nos ha traído grandes momentos, gracias a l@s excelentes ponentes que nos han ayudado a analizar y estudiar la #violenciadegénero. ¿quieres saber qué hemos aprendido?

la mesa redonda de análisis de las novedades legislativas - pacto de estado y ley andaluza - nos ha acercado el trabajo de juezas y fiscales, que nos han recordado que ya contamos con las leyes necesarias; lo que marcará la diferencia será su puesta en práctica.

a continuación hemos pasado al análisis de la masculinidad, con psicólogos y expertas en género, con los cuales hemos sido conscientes de todos los estímulos externos que recibimos, estableciendo roles de género desde que somos muy pequeñ@s.

en la siguiente mesa redonda hemos tratado el grave problema de la violencia de género en la industria audiovisual, y de cómo movimientos como #metoo han sembrado su impacto en españa.

también hemos contado con la celebración de foros paralelos para compartir experiencias. ¡mil gracias a tod@s l@s que habéis contribuido a que esta novena edición del congreso para el estudio de la violencia contra las mujeres haya sido todo un éxito! recordad que seguimos el debate en la fase virtual, y ¡nos vemos el año que viene!

text:
the contender _ senator laine billings hanson (2/2) happy #monologuethursday folks! needless to say, the inspiration for this piece didn't come by chance. these past days have been full of expectations and mixed feelings of hope and fear,  and i am so full of joy for how voters decided to show that inclusiveness, love and human rights matter. that we want to change the world for good. that that glass ceiling may not be unbearable, as long as we prove ourselves to be unbreakable.
that a world that protects democracy through strenght and love may be possible, if we have the strenght to stand for it.
together.
love,

text:
раннее детство моё пожалуй было беззаботным, я рано научилась читать и любила рисовать, так что проблем особых занять саму себя у меня не было))
воспитывала меня бабушка, которую я до определённого возраста называла мамой.... я отчётливо помню тот день когда я осознала что она не мама, а бабушка и попыталась позвать её "ба... бабушка... бабуль". мы обе плакали, это был странный и болезненный момент.
 настоящую мать я видела редко и называла её "мама алёна", что очень бесило её и она злилась на бабушку. бабуля говорит что мама очень ревновала нас и говорила:"ты ирку любишь больше чем меня". ну так, между прочим, вместо "спасибо". бабуля много работала, но старалась уделять и мне время, мы играли когда она приходила домой, хотя я представляю сейчас её усталость!!
ах да, родилась я в алма-ате (сейчас алматы) так что алматинцам привет :) (вот наверное откуда моя сверхъестественная любовь к яблокам🙈) в алма-ате я жила в окружении родственников, но тогда я ещё не понимала как это важно, я обожала своего дядю, бабушкиного мужа володю и своих игрушечных обезъян. 
крутой поворот случился когда моя мать нашла себе сожителя и решила забрать меня к себе....
многие, и я сейчас в том числе считают это был жест, доказательство "смотрите как я могу, я вам всем нос утёрла". потому что забрала она меня не абы куда, а в питер! в прочем, для меня это было не важно. потому что здесь начался мой ад. отчим мне попался мягко говоря не из тех кого хочется назвать папой,  человек он был очень образованный, но очень жестокий и как мне кажется с садистским уклоном. но об этом позже. с самого первого дня меня стали приучать к ремню, углу, физическому труду и собственно "не реветь". я делала всю работу по дому кроме стирки (стирала стиральная машина) и готовки (к плите меня подпускали только чтобы её помыть, так что готовить я не умела очень долго)  убиралась я каждый день и это подвергалось проверке, если я где-то что-то плохо помыла или пропустила - ремень и заново всё перемывать. 
#7днейвоспоминаний #янебоюсьсказать #акварель #рисунок #подслушано #секрет #irinashost #watercolorpainting #watercolour #art_collective #artlife #artistsoninstagram #metoo #aquarelle #art

ах да, родилась я в алма-ате (сейчас алматы) так что алматинцам привет :) (вот наверное откуда моя сверхъестественная любовь к яблокам🙈) в алма-ате я жила в окружении родственников, но тогда я ещё не понимала как это важно, я обожала своего дядю, бабушкиного мужа володю и своих игрушечных обезъян. 
крутой поворот случился когда моя мать нашла себе сожителя и решила забрать меня к себе....
многие, и я сейчас в том числе считают это был жест, доказательство "смотрите как я могу, я вам всем нос утёрла". потому что забрала она меня не абы куда, а в питер! в прочем, для меня это было не важно. потому что здесь начался мой ад. отчим мне попался мягко говоря не из тех кого хочется назвать папой,  человек он был очень образованный, но очень жестокий и как мне кажется с садистским уклоном. но об этом позже. с самого первого дня меня стали приучать к ремню, углу, физическому труду и собственно "не реветь". я делала всю работу по дому кроме стирки (стирала стиральная машина) и готовки (к плите меня подпускали только чтобы её помыть, так что готовить я не умела очень долго)  убиралась я каждый день и это подвергалось проверке, если я где-то что-то плохо помыла или пропустила - ремень и заново всё перемывать.

! ах да , родилась я в алма-ате ( сейчас алматы ) так что алматинцам привет : ) ( вот наверное откуда моя сверхъестественная любовь к яблокам🙈 ) в алма-ате я жила в окружении родственников , но тогда я ещё не понимала как это важно , я обожала своего дядю , бабушкиного мужа володю и своих игрушечных обезъян . крутой поворот случился когда моя мать нашла себе сожителя и решила забрать меня к себе ... . многие , и я сейчас в том числе считают это был жест , доказательство `` смотрите как я могу , я вам всем нос утёрла '' . потому что забрала она меня не абы куда , а в питер ! text:
as a therapist, i have to work hard to keep my heart open and not bring my work home with me. i work primarily with women and as the #metoo movement continues to grow, i have been holding space for a lot more stories of sexual abuse, assault, harassment, etc. •
i try to remember the amazing men in my life (including my incredible partner and loving father) to help remind myself that there are good guys out there and there is still so much education to be done in our culture. •
may we continue to let our stories be told and may we especially share our stories with the men in our lives that we trust. i believe this will help to raise the awareness of what life is really like for women in our world and will help men become more aware of how their actions impact us and our culture. •
i hope this movement continues to help us heal and prevents our daughters from experiencing the traumas that so many of us have endured during our lives. •
may we all love the life we live...

text: for all those who think they are the only ones struggling. we are all dealing with similar challenges. no one is perfect or with out struggle. the worst part about parenting is when we feel alone and isolated, like no one else knows what we are going through, or beating ourselves up for not being good enough. we need more authentic sharing, more witnessing of our real home lives... it’s great to show nice pictures on line.. but we need more authentic sharing of our hard times too. family is the highest path i know, most challenging and most worth it all. i pray for all families to have the strength to stay together, rise above the struggles, yearn for and create break throughs, heal, become self realized and help others do the same. we are one human tribe, one being of divine source. may we receive the grace in stillness and surrender during the hardest of times. surrender now, allow this moment to be experienced fully as it is. perfection is revealed in silence and stopping of the following of mind. ❤️ #authentic#truth#metoo#youarenotalone#weallstruggle#waldorf#homeschooling#honoringourancestors#truth#surrender#selfrealization#selfinquiry#selflove#servicefromtheheart#unitehumanity#familylife#love#karma#dharma#transformation#surrender#lifewithchildren#modernfamily#ubuntufuture#phifractalfamily#yeshi_sol

text:
i’m late to write this, but i voted on monday. despite having been able to vote for the past seven years, this was my first time voting in a non-presidential election. jeez louise that’s embarrassing to admit. nevertheless, i did it! here are some of the things i voted for: 
_
i voted for the environment
because future generations deserve access to the same outdoor experiences that have so greatly enriched my life.
because not all resources are infinite, and we only get one shot at taking care of a planet.
because climate change disproportionally affects those in need.
and because the outdoor recreation economy comprises $887 billion in consumer spending annually, sustains 7.6 million american jobs, and generates $124.5 billion in federal, state, and local tax revenue. so investing in the outdoors is not only socially responsible, it’s financially necessary. 
_
i voted for women 
because american women in 2018 earn 80.5 cents to every man’s dollar, and it’s estimated that pay parity will not be reached until 2059.
because paid family leave (for both men and women) is still not always guaranteed in the us.
and because one in three american women still experience some form of sexual violence in their lifetime, and that’s just unacceptable. 
_
i voted for education 
because i was blessed to have primary school teachers who weren’t stressed about being underpaid and undersupplied, and were able to prepare me for a lifetime of intellectual inquiry. 
because a bachelor’s degree is a minimum requirement these days, and students shouldn’t have to be in debt for decades just to acquire one. 
and because the global average rate of return on education per capita is 9% for each additional year of school completed, so we know that investing in students works. 
_
i voted for health
because without adequate public health care, i wouldn’t be alive today. 
because without adequate public health care, my mother wouldn’t have watched me graduate college. 
and because if we had all-around better access to preventative health care, maybe she, and millions of others, would still be here.
_
tagging my sources.

it’s a wave of #timesup.  times up on not being heard.  or believed.  or on being minimized.  gender, race, sexual orientation or identity. 
on another note if you told me i would be running a multi 6 figure business from the mountains of colorado surrounded by a community that is loving, nurturing working with women in remembering who they really are and finding an incredible sense of confidence and self respect i would have laughed at you and probably snarled a little.

text:
november. affärerna fyllda med julpynt. somliga för, somliga emot.

men för alla ni som klagar, har ni någonsin tänkt på alla dem stackare som jobbar i affär, som kanske mot sin vilja, varje år, tvingas ställa upp dessa varor?

har ni någonsin tänkt er in i deras smärta? att motvilligt tvingas placera ut gran efter gran, även fast man gråter, skriker ut: "det är bara november!" som en slav piskar chefen dessa stackars anställda, som lätt kunde varit du, eller kanske en praktikant. tänk dig fasan.

att ställas mot allt man tror på. är detta rätt? år 2018? kan vi ha det så här? modern tortyr.

och du har mage att klaga på lite julpynt?
det är i alla fall inte du som får ställa upp det på hyllorna, redan i november, så tidigt som oktober i vissa affärer!! stöd mig nu i kampen: #räddaallaanställdasomtvingasenförtidigjul

text:
the world is shifting.🙌🏻
⠀
women are creating powerful movements by sharing their truths, encouraging each other to have strong (sometimes unpopular) opinions and the courage to smash through societal expectations. we are breaking boundaries standing up for what we want and what we believe, and doing it unapologetically. the stories women share serve not only to educate us on how to fight for our beliefs, but help us realize what those beliefs are and what is truly worth fighting for.⠀
⠀
to empower others, we need to know first how to love ourselves, how to be ourselves, and how to love and honour other women. when you feel love for yourself it sets you free to lift others up. and when we lift others up, that is when we truly help empower them in the highest sense of the word. ⠀
⠀
tag a woman who inspires you and lifts you up so i can follow their journey.💕

text: yayy, so this arrived in nyc. well, this is happening! i’m grateful for this streak of madness in me that believes in big things. a dream, a vision, or a relationship, nothing is impossible to make real and beautiful... if you want it. it only takes a fierce kind of faith. i’ve been called “relentlessly” patient, because mine is the active but unconditional kind. when you trust in god, it’s only time... all your desires will become reality. my vision is i’d become the kind of woman who is clear, conscious and free (from conditioned limitations or from bs: even my own). with the loss of two dear ones in 2017, i was faced with that question again: am i really free? what does freedom mean!? so this last year i enrolled a talented collaborator and photographer @jromanska, we gathered 20 beautiful women, drew out 20 truth-telling bold stories, had 4-5 photoshoots in different locations, shared tears and laughter, and produced a book that will break the rules + tell the truth to freedom. you’ll be blown away. be free. keep faith. join us in nyc: www.bit.ly/freefemgala (link in bio)! #newyork #newyorkcity #goddess #freedom #magic #freefem #freefemproject #leadershipcoach #feminism #lifecoach #empoweringwomen #womensempowerment #loveisfree #rideordie #unconditionallove #friendship #sisterhood #changetheratio #growthmindset #leadership #courage  #losangeles #actionsspeaklouderthanwords #metoo #sanfrancisco #timesup

text:
“the women in my paintings are not based on any one specific female or feminine figure in my life but a plethora of many women. women have been a direct influence to a multitude of positive and significant transitions throughout my life experiences. especially in the direction towards an art career. in this present state i live in a world of massive gender inequality and i’m making it my personal responsibility as a man to use my voice creatively to bring attention and awareness to the strength, passion, resilience, innovation and beauty that women can offer to the world. if we allow women to receive equal opportunities and treatment there can only be amazing positivity and growth for us as human beings. the power of creation and the universe itself exists within the woman and without her we as humans could never be.

my voice stands with her voice, and each line i create builds a step towards equality for her.

#womenrock #womenwarriors
#womenarewarriors #lajonsart
#lajonspinkhairedmuse #ipaintwomen #pinkhairdontcare #gotpink #metoo #istandwithher #equalopportunity #herpower #herstrength #hercourage #love2paint #blessedtocreate #cantstopwontstop #colorofbeauty #imanartist

what pleasure do such people derive when they molest children? what?

why? what? when? how?

i just need answers to these difficult questions!

text:
seeing a psychiatrist and a therapist for the past month or so has helped me immensely. if you’re having feeling of depression or anxiety, i urge you to reach out for professional help. it’s takes strength and trust, but just reach deep down and i’m sure you can find it.
🖤
and although i am seeking help and, it is helping. i still have my bad days, weeks and some are far worse than others. but my support system is strong and i am grateful for that. 🍂
on another note: the rocks at queens cliff in manly, australia were a dream. the colors alone, beautiful!

text:
i can change the world.
my assumptions are: you read that sentence, rolled your eyes and thought “oh great, now she’s kanye.” and that’s fine, but let’s confess that kanye did change the world, by the very fact that we’re talking about kanye. (and i promise, now we’re done talking about kanye! i’d rather be taylor swift, anyway.)
.
i see the dialogue happening now calling out for more compassion and understanding, and for honoring the diversity of the human experience, and it feels like there is an opportunity to discuss infant massage in a way that people are anxious to hear. in a world of so much distraction and isolation, we are learning how to better find safety and refuge within ourselves and how to find purpose. as we learn, we can also teach. we can teach our children autonomy over their bodies, what is a good touch, who is a safe person, how do they know their worth, what do they have to give, where can they turn for peace… these conversations must start with our children from the very beginning. you begin your child’s life as their safe center, and you are particularly placed to carry it until it transfers from your heart into their own. you can shape the conversation however you choose; let infant massage be the foundation for teaching the principles that you cherish. your words and your touch can be the foundation upon which you build a strong and resilient spirit within your child. all you need to do is open your mouth and your hands, and have a conversation.
.
can you feel it yet? do you feel the power that you hold, and the influence that you have? it’s much simpler than we understand, more powerful than we can ever know, and the world needs it more than we could ever see. i’d love to hear your thoughts in the comments so we can get this conversation started. together we can get to work changing the world.
.
#infantmassage #babymassage #teachthemyoung #kanye #taylorswift #babies #metoo #massage #bethechange #starttalking

text:
meet our team! 
sophie is the project’s developer and director. she’s a belgian-american who earned a film, international development, and women’s studies degree from @mcgillu before moving to toronto in 2016. she’s worked as a journalist for the @thetorontostar, a producer for @sidlee_official, a publicity coordinator for @wearealphapr, & is currently casting ads and short films with @jigsawcasting. 
after being assaulted and beaten in toronto just weeks after she moved here, she has done what she can to change the dialogue around assault. 
she promoted documentary about mandi gray’s legal struggle against her rapist, @slutornutthemovie, ahead of its ultimately-soldout hot docs premiere, was asked to speak on a podcast about the kavanaugh confirmation, and is a writer for @ramonaforgirls, publishing pieces several times a year - under pseudonym sophie rose - about life after trauma.

she started the survivor project because she wanted to keep facilitating change around how people talk, conceive of, manage, and contextualize assault. she has a dedication to finding ways for assault survivors of all backgrounds and creeds to heal, grow, and feel less alone. the project aims to give toronto survivors a space, a community, and a voice. 
#thesurvivorproject #women #inspirational #strong #blackandwhite #film #toronto #metoo #meet #meetandgreet #woman

was it good, exciting, full of adventures or is a time you don't want to remember?

how then do you want your children to remember theirs?

this is me. tamalin srisook-polo , the founder of savoir agency and the creator of the savoir collab series.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
a little about me:⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1. i've been in experiential events for 15 yrs.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
2. my first big client was found on craigslist. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
3. i was the first producer on beautycon when it was a scrappy little idea.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
4. the craziest project was hiring 50 mila jovovich look-alikes for comic con.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
5. i grew up in diamond bar about 30miles east of la.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
6. i'm a gemini with a scorpio rising. (don't judge me)⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
7. i am a mother to a 20 something before i was 20 something.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
8. i'm all about using events as a vessel to connect with your target audience⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
9. my passion is empowering and helping women.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
10. my 5yr plan includes- paying off my daughter's horrendous student loans, grow my community savoir collab nationwide and run a thriving transparent agency where every single woman has a seat at the table!⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

no bo ja to nadal myślę. to zawsze jest złe i przeca powinno się pomóc…🌭🌭 👩‍🏫 zazwyczaj jest tak, że gdy mówimy o przemocy seksualnej, to myślimy o kobiecie jako ofierze i mężczyźnie jako sprawcy. gdy poszukujemy statystyk czy publikacji na ten temat, znajdziemy wiele dotyczących takiej konfiguracji i znacznie mniej dotyczących przemocy wobec mężczyzn. jednak z tych nielicznych badań, które można znaleźć*, wynika, że problem przemocy seksualnej dotyczy obu płci, czasem nawet w podobnym stopniu. nieprawdą jest, że „mężczyzny nie można zgwałcić”. oczywiście, że można. 🌭 teee, to dlaczego tak mało się o tym mówi, co? 👩‍🏫 dlatego, że jest to temat tabu. nasza kultura narzuca wzorzec „męskości”, który sprawia, że bycie ofiarą postrzegane jest jako oznaka słabości i powód do wstydu. mężczyźni, którzy doświadczają jakiejkolwiek formy przemocy i skarżą się na ten fakt, często spotykają się z drwinami dotyczącymi ich seksualności. może to prowadzić do tego, że taka osoba nie będzie chciała zgłosić przemocy. dlatego takie badania są mniej popularne, a oficjalne statystyki mogą być zaniżone. 🌭 czyli co, powinniśmy mówić więcej o przemocy seksualnej wobec chłopaków? 👩‍🏫 uważam, że w ogóle powinniśmy częściej rozmawiać o przemocy, a ona ma wiele twarzy. zazwyczaj mówimy o przemocy mężczyzn wobec kobiet lub wobec dzieci. ale prawda jest taka, że istnieje także przemoc (również seksualna) kobiet wobec mężczyzn, mężczyzn wobec mężczyzn, kobiet wobec kobiet i kobiet wobec dzieci. jeśli przełamiemy tabu, łatwiej będzie nam z tym walczyć. *jakby ktoś chciał więcej poczytać to piszcie, opowiemy o wynikach naszych poszukiwań i podeślemy linki!

jag blir så arg och frustrerad över hur vissa män i denna bransh ser på kvinnor och hur de beter sig mot dem. att kvinnor ska behöva gå igenom saker som inte är acceptabelt. det är sjukt. att personer i deras omgivning och som de har arbetat med inte har brytt sig om vad som har hänt, utan istället ha kommit med en massa ursäkter. att se kvinnor som ett objekt är fruktansvärt fel, hemskt och vidrigt. 
ni kvinnor i denna bransch är så coola och bra. sluta aldrig med det ni gör. ni gör skillnad. ni är hjältar. ni skrev historia. jag är så stolt att ha ida som förebild å ser väldigt mycket upp till henne. det var allt. förlåt för långt inlägg men tycker detta är viktigt. ha en fortsatt bra dag ❤ @idaengv #tystnadtagning #silenceaction #metoo

text:
here’s a snippet of a song we wrote awhile back but only started playing out recently. it’s about good men who sometimes behave badly, and how we often want to look the other way, because the action doesn’t mesh with the concept of the man we think we know, or taking action would upend too many structures on which we comfortably rely. it happens in churches, in jobs, in families—in places to which we have turned for refuge and support. when the silence and excuses wear off or become unbearable, maybe you tell the story to a trusted friend. or maybe you write a song about it. this is ours. “...they all say i’m fragile
with a touch of the blues
but i won’t be your pet
and babe you don’t want to be my muse

excuse me for asking
but it’s worth measuring my friend
do you know how many
tales of woe
you are starring in?

you’re a humble man
just a humble man
the fates have already forgiven you
you’re a humble man
just a humble man
and i am the woman 
who humbled you...” #metoo
name: Sister Sinjin

text:
jupiter into sagittarius ✧ jupiter is the planet of growth, abundance, expansion, prosperity, and joy, and today our largest planet in the solar system has officially moved into its home sign of ♐️ sagittarius! 💫⠀
⠀
after a year of moving through the sign of ♏️ scorpio, where it has helped promote the rising up of the spiritual entrepreneur 🙌🏼 and brought to light taboo issues that we're normally not comfortable facing in the light of day (such as the growing popularity of shadow work and the famous #metoo movement among others), jupiter now gives us a new collective focus for our growth.⠀
⠀
sagittarius is the wide-eyed visionary and the sign of travel, learning, teaching, and publishing, and this sign will be broadening our worldview by helping us discover new places and subjects as we soak up sage wisdom from those who are different, exotic, or foreign to us in order to reconnect the globe. 🌎⠀
⠀
the sign change of jupiter is a magical and momentous occasion that only happens once per year as it signals a whole new area of growth for each of us to receive new blessings and opportunities around for the coming 12.5 months.⠀
⠀
>> for more details on how this shift will be bringing blessings to your zodiac sign specifically, stay tuned for your november career scope (nearly ready to be published, a little late due to another very exciting project launching next week)! 🌟⠀

text:
aktion - minns #metoo

idag den 8:e november är det dags att uppmärksamma årsdagen av metoo-uppropet #tystnadtagning, sveriges första av därefter åtskilliga metoo-upprop som vittnade om omfattningen av sexuella trakasserier och sexuellt våld inför media och samhället. 
fi malmö kommer på grund av årsdagen utföra en #metoo-aktion, där vi tydliggör vikten av den kamp som ständigt fortskrider i påverkan av det metoo har visualiserat. 
idag hänger vi upp skyltar i olika träd runt om i centrala delar av malmö. på dessa skyltar står det olika metoo-hashtags, med samtliga av de metoo-upprop som skapats sedan rörelsens start i sverige nedskrivna. 
tanken är att dessa hashtags ska påminna oss hur många uppropen var, hur många kvinnor och ickebinära som blivit utsatta, hur många som fortfarande blir utsatta samt hur många fler som kommer bli utsatta i framtiden om vi inte sätter ett stopp för detta nu.

ett år efter #tystnadtagning har problemet blivit  avpolitiserat och lämnat den politiska dagordningen. det tänker inte vi acceptera.

vi feminister vill uppmuntra alla att hjälpa oss med att göra denna aktion ännu synligare genom att be er att göra egna skyltar och hänga upp i ert grannområde. välj en metoo-hashtag och skriv en egen lapp och häng upp den i ditt favorit träd! 
genom denna aktionen vill vi uppnå medvetenhet, organisering och ett kärleksfullt syskonskap. vi vill dessutom uppmuntra andra organisationer som arbetar med mänskliga rättigheter att delta i aktionen. 
tillsammans kan vi uppmärksamma den fortsatta problematiken, skapa motstånd och se till att detta aldrig kan osynliggöras igen!
den feministiska kampen fortsätter! ✊🏾
name: Feministiskt Initiativ Malmö

text:
tanzania has one of the highest rates of child marriages in the entire world. today, 37% of girls are forced into marriage before they have reached their 18th birthday. in fact, 2 out of 5 girls are married before they are 18 years old. traditional customs condone harassment and violence towards women. cases of violence usually go unreported. the cases that are reported are usually settled outside of court. discrimination also happens inside the classroom. the girls who actually get the chance to go to school can be automatically expelled if they are married or pregnant. in rural villages women who are older in years get accused of being witches and then are violently attacked. studies have shown that in 2013, 505 women in tanzania had witchcraft-related murders.

this is why the rafiki exchange strives to help widows in africa, including tanzania. we teach these women the bible. they now have an opportunity to learn about a loving god who sent his son to die for sinners, the one who created the world, a god who knows their every need. the rafiki exchange gives an opportunity for women to work and support themselves and their children. giving them an option which was nearly impossible before. we believe in helping women in need across africa. women who often times have no voice, women who are forgotten. we are passionate about this important work.
•
•
•
#africa #tanzania #tanzaniawomen #women #woman #voiceforthevoiceless #helpingothers #rafiki #rafikiexchange #african #metoo

text:
forced marriages, sexual abuse, and wife inheritance is all prevalent in the 8 million widows living in kenya. when you consider that kenya has some of the most oppressed widows in the world living in it, those 8 million lives suddenly seem to be more important. in a study done in 2016 the widows in kenya were ranked 33rd in the world for most devastated lifestyle. 
when her husband dies, the in-laws usually try and take the land from the widow he leaves behind. if the widow's land is taken from her by the in-laws, what choice does she have but to comply? if she protests them taking the land and takes the matter to court, what will happen if she wins? she will have a home but will then be completely ostracized by her clan. she may have four walls and a roof over her head, but living in a village where no one will speak to you would be a tragic life. it seems far safer to let them take the home and property. 
in most cases, widows end up blamed for their husband's death and cast out of society with no belongings. with no property, no home, and no one to turn to for help, the widow is left alone. 
this is why rafiki's work with widows is so important. we come along side these women and help them support themselves in a way that was not possible before. it is our hope that you will come along side of us and help give lasting hope to future generations of widows in kenya. •
•
•
•
