text:
in 1994 the finish of the rwandan genocide, which came from a 100 day mass murder from the hutu and tutsi tribes, left over 800,000 people dead. studies show that 1 in 10 rwandans died during these 100 days. the effects of having almost 1 million people die in less than four months is staggering. rwanda quickly became a country with more women than men. the scars and trauma these women carry with them is both tragic and inspiring. they survived things most of us couldn’t even dream of. they watched their children and husbands get hacked into bits by men with machetes, or were trapped while their neighbors were violently clubbed to death. their homes were destroyed and burned to the ground while they were forced to watch. for a lot of these women, what they went through after watching this unfold, would be what some would call a fate worse than death. violent rapings were condoned and these women suffered in the most extreme ways because of it. some were left after all this took place to, “die of sadness.” after the genocide finished, these widows were left to pick up the pieces, and somehow make a new life. with their husbands dead, the widows from the hutu and tutsi tribes came together and made peace. by weaving baskets together these women found a way of healing in something that has been a part of rwandan culture for centuries. the weaving and selling of these baskets to western markets has gained the rwandan widows economic independence and improved their local communities. 
now, 24 years later, 50% of homes in rwanda are run by women. the women in this country still live in extreme poverty. often $1.25 a day or less is what they have to feed and shelter themselves and their children. they are slowly rebuilding. the rafiki exchange has partnered with these very women, and are selling their baskets in our local exchanges, on our online exchange, and our new etsy shop. we are passionate about helping these widows support themselves and their children. this is work that you can be apart of. click the link in our bio to shop the rafiki exchange and support these widows in rwanda. •
•
•
•

now, 24 years later, 50% of homes in rwanda are run by women. the women in this country still live in extreme poverty. often $1.25 a day or less is what they have to feed and shelter themselves and their children. they are slowly rebuilding. the rafiki exchange has partnered with these very women, and are selling their baskets in our local exchanges, on our online exchange, and our new etsy shop. we are passionate about helping these widows support themselves and their children. this is work that you can be apart of. click the link in our bio to shop the rafiki exchange and support these widows in rwanda. •
•
•
•
#widows #rwanda #rwandangenocide #baskets #peace #unity #africa #metoo

text:
widowhood in uganda is a hardship that most of us cannot possibly fathom—11% of women over 15 years old are widows. studies show that 50% of these widows are illiterate, 67% work in other people’s gardens for survival, and 61% survive on less than 5,000 ugandan shillings a week–less than two american dollars. shortly after her husband dies, the widow is subjected to the common ugandan practice of “property grabbing.” this is the intentional driving out of the vulnerable woman and her dependents from their homes and land by physical force, threats, intimidation, and property destruction. studies have shown that over 18% of widows that go through property grabbing have also experienced attempts on their lives. even so, the women cling tenaciously to their homes and property. why wouldn’t they? their children need shelter—a place to lay their heads at night and carry on in life. in spite of their resistance to the property grabbing, 17% still see their homes and property viciously destroyed in the process. the plight of the ugandan widows is unconscionable.
•
•
•

text:
my sister @stealthlikemi and huzzband @unityofnoise have a new heart wrenching song being released tomorrow. my sister has been struggling with multiple hardships emotionally, down to the cellular level. trying to still function in a world that doesn’t stop spinning to allow her the time to grab a hold of her health. when things are looking up they take another left turn. we as a family support her and help as much as we can from a distance. 
tomorrow when the song gets released my family is getting the semi-colon tattooed on ourselves... as we all can relate to it’s new meaning and also in support of my sisters struggles. we have all been there at some point in our lives. just thankful at different times so we can be a rock for others when needed. 
project semicolon, which offers hope to those struggling with depression, suicide, addiction and self-injury, borrows its philosophy from the punctuation mark in its name. “a semicolon is used when an author could've chosen to end their sentence, but chose not to,” the project's website reads. “the author is you and the sentence is your life.” i have lost friends to suicide and addiction. i have personally struggled with anxiety and depression. my sisters song and jim’s minimal production really hits me deep in my soul. 
i hope you all connect and have a listen, and support not only music, but my sisters form of art work. $1 for a song, to own a piece of artwork seems crazy right?
music is taken for granted more then ever, and people expect it for free when it takes years of time, energy and emotional release to finish a piece of music. not only that, but it is like winning the lottery to make a living off of music these days, so while my sister is a true artist, she losses herself when she goes to her corporate job that can support her family and retain benefits. 
the struggle is real. what would the world be without artists? #newmusic #amazonmusic #itunesmusic #spotify #alternative #singer  #songwriter #femalesongwriter #producer #unityofnoise #harp #strings #piano  #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealth #semicolon #semicolonart #semicolontattoo #semicolonproject @sufferingthesilence #afsp #metoo @reborn.social @
name: Melis Fusco

my sister @stealthlikemi and huzzband @unityofnoise have a new heart wrenching song being released tomorrow. my sister has been struggling with multiple hardships emotionally, down to the cellular level. trying to still function in a world that doesn’t stop spinning to allow her the time to grab a hold of her health. when things are looking up they take another left turn. we as a family support her and help as much as we can from a distance. 
tomorrow when the song gets released my family is getting the semi-colon tattooed on ourselves... as we all can relate to it’s new meaning and also in support of my sisters struggles. we have all been there at some point in our lives. just thankful at different times so we can be a rock for others when needed. 
project semicolon, which offers hope to those struggling with depression, suicide, addiction and self-injury, borrows its philosophy from the punctuation mark in its name. “a semicolon is used when an author could've chosen to end their sentence, but chose not to,” the project's website reads. “the author is you and the sentence is your life.” i have lost friends to suicide and addiction. i have personally struggled with anxiety and depression. my sisters song and jim’s minimal production really hits me deep in my soul. 
i hope you all connect and have a listen, and support not only music, but my sisters form of art work. $1 for a song, to own a piece of artwork seems crazy right?
music is taken for granted more then ever, and people expect it for free when it takes years of time, energy and emotional release to finish a piece of music. not only that, but it is like winning the lottery to make a living off of music these days, so while my sister is a true artist, she losses herself when she goes to her corporate job that can support her family and retain benefits. 
the struggle is real. what would the world be without artists? #newmusic #amazonmusic #itunesmusic #spotify #alternative #singer  #songwriter #femalesongwriter #producer #unityofnoise #harp #strings #piano  #mentalhealthawareness #mentalhealth #semicolon #semicolonart #semicolontattoo #semicolonproject @sufferingthesilence #afsp #metoo @reborn.social @

text: panic attacks - anxiety - depression i’ve been through it all. it certainly doesn’t help when you continually search for help online and find yourself faced with nothing. i remember a young lady once said to me that she didn’t like the word disfigurement and preferred visible difference. i replied to her that i don’t have a visible difference so yes i have a disfigurement or hidden difference (which i don’t like). my point is....anyone is allowed to give themselves a name or word that fits their description on how they look but please do not tell someone what word they should be using. if my scars were visible then that word would be ok but my life has been plagued with self body hating because my scars were always undercover covered up! just because my scars were covered it doesn’t mean i was ok. if i was ok i certainly would not be sharing my story 40-50 years later #metoomovement #metoo #bopo #bodypositive #timesup #loveswimming #inclusionmatters #diversityandinclusion #bodydiversity #swimchallenge #campaigners @adidas_swim @swimwear365 @swimengland @better_uk @thisgirlcanuk @virginactiveuk ❤️👌🏼

text:
we are a collective of survivors and allies in toronto working to help heal those affected by sexual assault. 
december 2018 - a safe space for toronto survivors to gather in small numbers and partake in food, art, company, and affirmation. those who wish to tell their stories, speak their truths, read letters, vent, & more are encouraged to spend time in our recording booth, where they are given a platform and a voice they may have felt they were lacking. 
2019 - a short film, based on and around the anonymous testimony given by survivors during the event. 
this is to help the survivors of every age, race, creed, sexuality, status who’ve felt helpless, voiceless, angry, upset, triggered during this period in which #metoo and rape culture has been so prevalently public. this is to help disseminate information and affect about the range and reality of assault in our city. this is to help us understand where our culture’s going wrong. this is to help however we can. 
if you have questions, or if you’d like to be involved, please be in touch. 
information on the event coming very soon 🖤

text:
🤭 okay so the immature side or the prudish side, not sure which, may squirm uneasily in my seat. but i ask myself why is that❓ ❗the people pleaser in me, says don't post it, you'll offend someone. ❗the 'need to justify' in me, says don't post it, people will think you hate men. i don't. ❗the 'girl' in me says don't post it, you'll be called a slag. ✊🏽the women in me posted it. 
why? no it's not because i love talking about sex. in fact, i'm quite private when it comes to affairs of the bedroom. (just the fact i referred to it as affairs of the bedroom is evidence alone!)
i'm private because i choose to be not because i'm ashamed. as always, each to their own, no judgement here.

i posted it because it is a fair point to be made. women can't casually refer to their sexual pleasure as men do, as their simply isn't the language to do so. it's not that i'm saying i think we should all shout about 'getting off', like i said, i'm private... i suppose i'm using it as a vehicle to highlight how, if the choice of  vocabulary is there, it can have a significant impact on the way we perceive, think and accept situations/ideas. without the vocab we cannot express=only one angle exposed. what choice does that leave? "the way we think is so related to language" so if their isn't the language how do we learn to expand our thinking?

thank you to @theonly_louaimeshill
for sharing this! 🤔 and @holliepoetry
for giving me the words.
i feel a blog post coming on!! 📝

name: Raising A Rebel
tweet_full:
🤭 okay so the immature side or the prudish side, not sure which, may squirm uneasily in my seat. but i ask myself why is that❓ ❗the people pleaser in me, says do not post it, you'll offend someone. ❗the 'need to justify' in me, says do not post it, people will think you hate men. i do not. ❗the 'girl' in me says do not post it, you'll be called a slag. ✊🏽the women in me posted it. 
why? no it is not because i love talking about sex. in fact, i am quite private when it comes to affairs of the bedroom. (just the fact i referred to it as affairs of the bedroom is evidence alone!)
i am private because i choose to be not because i am ashamed. as always, each to their own, no judgement here.

i posted it because it is a fair point to be made. women can not casually refer to their sexual pleasure as men do, as their simply is not the language to do so. it is not that i am saying i think we should all shout about 'getting off', like i said, i am private... i suppose i am using it as a vehicle to highlight how, if the choice of  vocabulary is there, it can have a significan not impact on the way we perceive, think and accept situations/ideas. without the vocab we cannot express=only one angle exposed. what choice does that leave? "the way we think is so related to language" so if their is not the language how do we learn to expand our thinking?

thank you to @theonly_louaimeshill
for sharing this! 🤔 and @holliepoetry
for giving me the words.
i feel a blog post coming on!! 📝

text:
we're joining in with #museum30 this month and today is ‘controversial'. for today's museum30 we’re sharing a post from our girl reviews series, in which contributing writer michelle o’brien writes: "this plot point is troublesome for a number of reasons. the first is that jake views caroline is his property and he can trade her for something that he wants. if he cared at all about his girlfriend he would have made sure she got home safely. the second issue is that the geek gives her still more alcohol and takes pictures with her so he has proof of his “conquest”. caroline was already drunk and did not want or need any more alcohol; additionally, taking photos without her consent is unacceptable. the third problem stems from caroline waking up without any memory of what happened, and yet she says that she feels likes she enjoyed herself. we don’t see what happened between caroline and the geek, but it is implied they had sex. even though she doesn’t remember it and she was too drunk to consent, this is never addressed by her or ted. it implies that this sort of behaviour is acceptable and it simply is not.
i was in college the first time i watched this movie and i found the entire movie problematic (honestly i disliked every character). if i had watched this when i was younger and more impressionable it could have had a much bigger impact on me. with the #metoo and #timesup movements reviewing problematic portrayals of women on tv and in movies has become a popular topic. if you are interested in reading more about this i strongly recommend reading molly ringwald’s article where she goes into far more detail on this topic." read the fill blog at http://girlmuseum.org

text:
registration link given in bio. 'ਸਿਆਸੀ ਤੌਰ 'ਤੇ ਗ਼ਲਤ'- ਭਾਸ਼ਣ ਮੁਕਾਬਲਾ
ਮੁਕਾਬਲੇ ਬਾਰੇ  ਸੰਖੇਪ - 
ਕੱਲ੍ਹ ਦੇ ਆਗੂ ਹੋਣ ਵਜੋਂ ਅਤੇ ਅੱਜ ਦੇ ਸਮਾਜ ਦੇ ਰੂਪ ਵਿੱਚ ਸਾਡਾ ਫਰਜ਼ ਬਣਦਾ ਹੈ ਕਿ ਅਸੀਂ ਉਹਨਾਂ ਮਸਲਿਆਂ ਬਾਰੇ ਖੁੱਲ੍ਹ ਕੇ ਗੱਲ ਕਰੀਏ ਜੋ ਪ੍ਰਸ਼ਾਸਨ ਦੁਆਰਾ  ਮੀਡੀਆ, ਤਾਕਤ ਅਤੇ ਜਨਤਕ ਪ੍ਰਭਾਵ ਰਾਹੀਂ ਦਬਾਅ ਦਿੱਤੇ ਜਾਂਦੇ ਹਨ।
ਇਹ ਮੁਕਾਬਲਾ ਵਿਦਿਆਰਥੀ ਨੂੰ ਵਿਸ਼ਾ ਬਾਰੇ ਆਪਣੇ ਖਿਆਲਾਂ ਨੂੰ ਪ੍ਰਗਟ ਕਰਨ ਅਤੇ ਸਹੀ ਸਾਬਤ ਕਰਦੇ ਹੋਏ ਜਿੱਤ ਦਵਾਏਗਾ ।
ਅੰਕਾਂ ਦਾ ਮਾਪਦੰਡ
ਪੇਸ਼ਕਾਰੀ ਅਤੇ ਭਾਸ਼ਾਈ - 10
ਹਾਵ-ਭਾਵ ਅਤੇ ਆਵਾਜ਼ ਦਾ ਫੇਰਬਦਲ - 10
ਵਿਚਾਰ ਦੀ ਸਪੱਸ਼ਟਤਾ - 10
ਵਿਅੰਗ ਅਤੇ ਨਵੀਨਤਾ -20
ਵਿਸ਼ੇ
1) ਕੀ ਬੁੱਤਾਂ ਅਤੇ ਢਾਂਚਿਆਂ 'ਤੇ ਸਰਕਾਰ ਦੇ ਖਰਚੇ ਜਾਇਜ਼ ਹਨ?
2) ਸ਼ਹਿਰਾਂ, ਸਟੇਸ਼ਨਾਂ ਅਤੇ ਸਥਾਨਾਂ ਦੇ ਨਾਮਕਰਨ 'ਤੇ ਦੇਸ਼ ਦੀ ਪ੍ਰਤੀਕਿਰਿਆ
3) ਮੀਟੂ - ਇੱਕ ਅੰਦੋਲਨ, ਭਾਰਤ ਹਜ਼ਮ ਨਹੀਂ ਕਰ ਸਕਦਾ.
4) 2019 ਚੋਣਾਂ ਕਿਵੇਂ ਲੜੇ ਜਾਣਗੀਆਂ ਅਤੇ ਜਿੱਤੀਆਂ ਜਾਣਗੀਆਂ?
ਸਪੀਚ
a) ਭਾਗੀਦਾਰ ਕਿਸੇ ਵੀ ਇੱਕ ਵਿਸ਼ੇ ਨੂੰ ਚੁਣ ਸਕਦਾ ਹੈ।
ਬੀ) ਭਾਸ਼ਣ ਦਾ ਸਮਾਂ 3 ਤੋਂ 5 ਮਿੰਟ ਤੱਕ ਦਾ ਹੋਵੇਗਾ. ਪਹਿਲੀ ਘੰਟੀ 3 ਵਜੇ ਅਤੇ ਫਿਰ ਦੂਜੀ 4.30 ਵਜੇ 
c) 5 ਮਿੰਟ ਦਾ ਸਮਾਂ ਲੰਘਣ ਵਾਲੇ ਨੂੰ ਅਯੋਗ ਕਰਾਰ ਦੇ ਦਿੱਤਾ ਜਾਵੇਗਾ.
ਭਾਸ਼ਾ
ਕੋਈ ਭਾਸ਼ਾ ਦਾ ਕੋਈ ਅੜਿੱਕਾ ਨਹੀਂ ਹੈ । ਭਾਸ਼ਣ ਪੰਜਾਬੀ, ਹਿੰਦੀ ਜਾਂ ਅੰਗਰੇਜ਼ੀ ਵਿੱਚ ਹੋ ਸਕਦਾ ਹੈl

politically incorrect - the declmation competition 
competition brief - as being the leaders of tomorrow and the society of today,  it is our duty to openly dicuss issues which have been suppressed by the authorities by way of media,  power and public influence. 
the competition will let the student express his/her heart out over the topic and win the show by standing vindicated.

criteria of marking

presentation and oratory - 10
expression and voice modulation - 10
clarity of thought - 10
satire and novelty - 20

topics

1) are government's expenditures on statues and structures justified? 
2) nation's reaction on renaming of cities,  stations and places.

3) #metoo - a movement india couldn't digest. 
4) how will 2019 elections be fought and won? 
speech

a)  the participant can chose any one topic and declaim the same. 
b)  the time for the speech shall be from 3 to 5 minutes. the first bell will ring at 3 and then at 4.30.
c)  crossing 5 minutes will amount to disqualification.

language 
there is no language bar - the speech can be in punjabi,  hindi or english. but the speech cannot be bilingual, if the speech is english.

politically incorrect - the declmation competition 
competition brief - as being the leaders of tomorrow and the society of today,  it is our duty to openly dicuss issues which have been suppressed by the authorities by way of media,  power and public influence. 
the competition will let the student express his/her hea out over the topic and win the show by standing vindicated.

criteria of marking

presentation and oratory - 10
expression and voice modulation - 10
clarity of thought - 10
satire and novelty - 20

topics

1) are government's expenditures on statues and structures justified? 
2) nation's reaction on renaming of cities,  stations and places.

3)  - a movement india couldn't digest. 
4) how will 2019 elections be fought and won? 
speech

a)  the paicipant can chose any one topic and declaim the same. 
b)  the time for the speech shall be from 3 to 5 minutes. the first bell will ring at 3 and then at 4.30.
c)  crossing 5 minutes will amount to disqualification.

language 
there is no language bar - the speech can be in punjabi,  hindi or english. but the speech cannot be bilingual, if the speech is english.

text_retweet:
#repost @feministerna
・・・
f! inrättar minnesdag för patriarkatets offer 
ett år har passerat sedan #metoo slog ner i sverige. alla var överens. det var oacceptabelt, åtgärder måste vidtas.
men, som oftast i frågor som rör jämställdhet och feminism, är steget från ord till handling oerhört långt. ett antal symboliska justeringar gjordes i regeringens budget, däremot lyser genomgripande reformer eller myndighetsdirektiv med sin frånvaro.

istället är det just nu snarare en backlash som sticker ut mest i det offentliga samtalet. debatten domineras av kränkta män, en nyväckt konservativ våg av röster som drömmer om hemmafrutillvaro och okunnigt hummande om ”genusflum”, samt den återkommande häpnadsväckande åsikten att ”det har gått för långt”, med #metoo, med jämställdheten, med mänskliga rättigheter.

som om vittnesmålen försvunnit i en kollektiv minnesförlust. feministiskt initiativ har inte glömt. därför gör vi nu den 8 november till en nationell minnesdag och dedicerar hela månaden november till att minnas, hedra och visa uppskattning för de många metoo-uppropen”, skriver gita nabavi och gudrun schyman. →läs hela artikeln här: https://www.svt.se/opinion/vi-kommer-att-ga-sa-langt-som-det-kravs?fbclid=iwar2hqhk2zb0xczynoa4ww-3wzvsr1o9lxmpk_oehjjdu6i62jfpxcoyp-yw

text:
dear agni,
.
kamu tidak sendiri. saya juga penyintas.
di usia 4 tahun, saya dicabuli oleh sepupu sendiri.
tapi saya diam, sebab saya tidak tahu apa yang dia lakukan.
.
kamu tidak sendiri. saya juga korban.
di usia 10 tahun, seorang tukang becak menyekap saya di lorong sekolah, dan menjamah liang senggama saya.
saya cuma mingkem, sebab saya takut dianggap tidak bisa jaga diri.
.
kamu tidak sendiri. saya pernah dilecehkan.
di usia 17 tahun, saya bersepeda di jalanan sepi sambil memakai celana training dan hoodie. tiba-tiba seorang bapak menepuk pantat saya.
saya terdiam, karena ketakutan dan tidak bisa bereaksi apa-apa.
.
dear agni,
.
saya tahu rasanya, karena #sayajuga mengalaminya. mau melawan, tapi merasa tidak berdaya. mau mengadu, tapi takut dibikin malu. mau marah-marah sambil membanting, tapi orang tidak pernah menganggap ini penting.
.
sekarang karenamu, keberanian ini bertunas, agni!
suaramu melengking, memekakkan telinga, menerobos batas-batas timpangnya keadilan. sumbu telah ditarik, dan terimakasih atas api yang kau pantik.
.
mulai hari ini dan seterusnya, kita kawal bersama rasa amanmu, rasa aman para wanita yang masih bersembunyi di balik besar dan kuatnya rasa takut. bukan saatnya untuk kita merasa lemah.
.
dan terima kasih paling besar buatmu karena telah menyadarkan bahwa kita bukan barang yang bisa disejajarkan dengan jamahan!
.
untuk semua wanita yang mengalami hal yang sama, kita adalah agni, dan kita adalah api!

#kitaagni
#metoo 
#sayajuga 
#kamibersamaagni ---

pre_proc_tweet:
dear agni,
.
kamu tidak sendiri. saya juga penyintas.
di usia 4 tahun, saya dicabuli oleh sepupu sendiri.
tapi saya diam, sebab saya tidak tahu apa yang dia lakukan.
.
kamu tidak sendiri. saya juga korban.
di usia 10 tahun, seorang tukang becak menyekap saya di lorong sekolah, dan menjamah liang senggama saya.
saya cuma mingkem, sebab saya takut dianggap tidak bisa jaga diri.
.
kamu tidak sendiri. saya pernah dilecehkan.
di usia 17 tahun, saya bersepeda di jala sepi sambil memakai celana training dan hoodie. tiba-tiba seorang bapak menepuk pantat saya.
saya terdiam, karena ketakutan dan tidak bisa bereaksi apa-apa.
.
dear agni,
.
saya tahu rasanya, karena  mengalaminya. mau melawan, tapi merasa tidak berdaya. mau mengadu, tapi takut dibikin malu. mau marah-marah sambil membanting, tapi orang tidak pernah menganggap ini penting.
.
sekarang karenamu, keberanian ini beunas, agni!
suaramu melengking, memekakkan telinga, menerobos batas-batas timpangnya keadilan. sumbu telah ditarik, dan terimakasih atas api yang kau pantik.
.
mulai hari ini dan seterusnya, kita kawal bersama rasa amanmu, rasa aman para wanita yang masih bersembunyi di balik besar dan kuatnya rasa takut. bukan saatnya untuk kita merasa lemah.
.
dan terima kasih paling besar buatmu karena telah menyadarkan bahwa kita bukan barang yang bisa disejajarkan dengan jamahan!
.
untuk semua wanita yang mengalami hal yang sama, kita adalah agni, dan kita adalah api!

text:
<heart> 
writing the truth is hard. but it's also the most powerful thing. 
i don't always believe in what i see, i also don't believe in what i hear. i believe in my heart. ❤️
despite all the turmoils, loss, and heartbreaks i've lived through up until now, my heart is still alive. 
i wasn't planning to go this direction when i started this post, but here i am. 
i believe that the heart can re-grow, expand, into a stronger state than she's ever been. i need to constantly feed her a lot of love, and a lot of love she deserves and needs. 
not every moment in life is perfect. but it's not going to change if i don't face it. i believe in change, and i always believe that love is love. 💔❤️

text:
our soars 20th anniversary tour continues..next stop, atlanta georgia! we are headed to atlanta for the national women’s association conference @nwsa_ig !! the spoken-word poet you see on stage, anaya patrice frazier, girl/friend youth leader, who performed a poem this summer about the missing & murdered black girls on the south & west side of chicago will be taking the stage with legendary reproductive justice organizer loretta ross,  national campus activist wagatwe wanjuki @wagatwe, revolutionary filmmaker @afrolez aisha simmons, radical black feminist photographer & youth community organizer @sherphotographs scheherazade tillet, writer, educator, and organizer @salamishah and girl/friends youth leader danielle nolen to y’all about “give my consent never: black women and girls revolutionizing the anti-rape movement.”
*
*
this panel will build off the concept from the combahee river collective statement, “if black women were free, it would mean that everyone else would have to be free,” & engages four generations of black women artists and activists to historicize and to reflect on the vanguard roles that they and others have played in the movement to end sexual violence before and beyond #metoo

#soars20 #gotconsent #nwsa
*

text:
“i’m a dreamer/a distant dreamer” — and i am crestfallen. another day, another tragic news story. i recorded this rough, little clip, with belle, on tuesday; election day. together, we were dreaming for a change. i don’t really play guitar for people. i don’t share these kinds of clips on here. my guitar is out of tune and my voice is hoarse. but, really? i’m reading the news and hearing stories of bravery and if people can be so freakin’ brave in so many real ways, i can post an instagram clip. i never intended to share this, but the words make so much sense to me today. this was just a tiny, real moment. a moment in time when my daughter and i shared a song; a cozy room; hope. something needs to change. stop the violence. just stop. ❤️

text:
a big shift happens today as the planet of expansion, jupiter, moves into it's own sign, sagittarius. ♐
--
jupiter's orbit takes 12 years to go around the sun, so it spends a year in each sign. --
it bids farewell to sexual scorpio today, where a year ago we saw it expand the #metoo movement. in sagittarius, the mood is more buoyant, optimistic, and firey.🔥
--
since jupiter (along with saturn) is a societal planet, we'll see a shift in society as a whole. perhaps more playful, like this beautiful stallion, black jack, doing tricks for treats. 🐎
--
care must be taken, however, to not get stuck in our own beliefs and become self-righteous and dogmatic. 🤔
--
the house jupiter is transiting is likely to expand and take on an added focus for the next year. it's in my 6th house of daily routine, work, health, and diet. where is sagittarius in your chart? 🏠
--
#jupiter #sagittarius #expansion #optimism #shift #stallion #astroyogawoman

text: the word movement, animal, and mobility coach is trending on instagram like a #metoo hashtag. if a coach or teacher can’t link the transition with a practical application they are probably just a trending opportunist rather than an movement educator. always understand the why rather than accepting the ambiguous what. too many people are claiming to teach “movement” technology without understanding the layers of application that comprise its unseen or invisible aspects that make it a truly useful tool. in brazilian jiu-jitsu there’s no hiding from the what, why and how. to learn more of the why join me for a budokon university training camp. info@budokon.com. #budokonyoga #bjj #bjjlifestyle #bjjgirls #movementculture #bjjmotivation #mma #fighters #yogainspiration

text:
🙋🏽‍♂️raise your hand + give it a ❤️ if you agree with this. although you’d probably guess that i’m an extrovert, i’m actually an introverted extrovert - this means i’m introverted by nature but choose to be extroverted for something i care about. 
__
i remember how much pressure i felt in my teenage years and early 20s, to fit into an extroverted party culture. 🕺🏽 all i wanted to do was stay at home with a warm blanket; casting circles, making crystal potions,🔮 and coming up with new tarot spreads. 
__
do you feel me, lightworker? 🙃please, say you do. not just to me, to others, too. many introverts are loners, so we naturally keep quiet about our concerns. but, i believe the more we talk about it the more we normalise it, and give permission to likeminded people 🧘🏾‍♀️ to embrace, rather than feel guilty about their introversion. 
__
tell me, do you also treasure your alone time? who suffers most when you don’t get it? 😝

text:
many of my clients wake up with overwhelming anxiety before they even start their day. they are constantly thinking about what they don’t have, what they are failing at, and worried about what others may think of them. 
as an empath, this lack mentality and negative thinking made my chest feel heavy just writing that out. it’s amazing how powerful our brains are. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this is why positivity is so peaceful and freeing. the heaviness from your chest is lifted. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
this type of behavior doesn’t come with a light switch you can just turn on and off. this isn’t an overnight fix. it’s a way of life. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
here are 5 simple reminders i would like you to start and end your day with.  reprogram your mind to think positive. you owe it to yourself. you deserve it 💜

text:
in may 2018 we officially launched she matters tribe in nairobi, kenya. we have seen our community grow to thousands of women from around the world. we’ve shared our stories, we’ve shared our struggles, and now we’re taking action. 
___
today we launch the she matters reporting platform. by survivors, for survivors. 
while we encourage all survivors to report sexual assault cases to police and seek medical treatment in hospital, we too understand that thousands of survivors worldwide face intolerance, disbelief, and insensitivity when reporting. 
far too many of us have been told we are not believed. 
far too many of us have been told “we looked like we enjoyed it”. far too many of us have been questioned about our level of alcohol consumption, or what we wore - as if that were justification for rape. 
we are here for you. 
the she matters reporting platform will allow you to report anonymously, or with your identity, malpractice or insensitivity from law enforcement or medical professionals when reporting sexual assault. 
we are holding our community stakeholders accountable, and working towards a strengthened system where we are believed and supported. 
___
your voice matters. 
you are not alone. 
we’re stronger together! [link in bio]
#shematters #strongertogether #metoo

text:
jupiter moves into sagittarius today.
.
.
.
he’s been settled in scorpio for the past 13 months, forcing us to uncover uncomfortable truths about death, sexuality, our darkness and shadows... it’s actually quite obvious when you look at it on the collective level—the advent of the #metoo movement, gender equality issues, etc.
.
jupiter in scorpio has been a lot. it’s been an exhausting adventure. so much darkness has been exposed to the light. you know when your eyes have adjusted to the darkness and you suddenly flip on the light and you’re like “oh god my eyes!” because it’s so bright and blinding? but then eventually your eyes readjust to the light and you start to see things for what they are? that’s kind of like this transition from jupiter in scorpio into jupiter in sag. the lights are on. sagittarius is the archer, aiming to open the mind and open the heart. sagittarius is expansive and good natured energy.
.
a caveat: there’s a challenging cosmic friction point coming up where mars will square jupiter in the middle of the month through the end of the year, so remain steadfast in your commitment to move forward into the light with as much positivity as you can possibly muster. find your strength and allow your new understanding of your shadows to propel you forth. as we make this transition out of the shadows and into the light, keep coming back to the lessons learned from the darkness.
.

in a nutshell: boldly ask the universe for what you want, and be open to all the ways in which it will provide. remember, an archer must draw his bow backward before it can fly forward. keep aiming. 🏹

text:
a woman asked me why i work out so i told her, “ if there is ever a situation where me and my children are in danger i want to be able to carry them for as long and as far as i need to to protect them.”
needless to say my answer shook her.
but here is my truth... i am a survivor of domestic violence, sexual assault, & incest.
yes my life is pretty great now. i have an amazing husband & 2 incredible kids... but i still look over my shoulder, i still sleep with the lights on, & i am still very distrusting of men.
i don’t workout because i am afraid, i work out so i can be fearless. 👊🏼 •
•
•

so i wanted to make a video to show everyone just how quick it is to bring gratitudes to your daily life.. - 
they are so powerful and they take less than 90 seconds... - 
less than 90 seconds and they are just as powerful as some depression medication?! - 
yep. - 
make time for these, i promise you won't regret it :) - 
watch the full video on youtube: overcoming ptsd

text:
lite foton från vårt frukostmingel om #metoo 1 år den 7 november, med bland annat skådespelaren eva röse, samhällsdebattören linnéa claeson, kulturminister alice bah kuhnke, rfsu:s förbundsordförande hans linde och tco:s ordförande eva nordmark. vi bjöd gästerna på vegetarisk frukostbuffé och @juiceverket fanns på plats för att servera nypressad fräsch juice. de medverkande fick som tack var sin blombukett gjord av av cupcakes. 💐🥤

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

if you donate even just $1, leave a comment or dm me and i'll send you a bff, beer food fun sticker to show my appreciation! thank you. 
#forthekids

text:
"artists again censorship and self censorship. the role of the female artists as agents for social change in diverse contexts of creation”. #xabaca 2018 with @sondosshabayek and @alaasatir . next monday at 19h in @iemed_bcn  in english with simultaneous translation. / “art i feminisme a la ciutat: el rol de les artistes en tant que agents de canvi social en contextos de creació diversos". l'escriptora, storyteller, performer i directora teatral @sondosshabayek (el caire) i fundadora de @thebussyproject i la il·lustradora @alaasatir (khartum) parlaran dels seus processos creatius estretament lligats als seus contextos específics en tant que dones artistes que s'erigeixen amb una veu pròpia que es revindica més enllà de la censura i l'autocensura.
xabaca (xarxa en àrab) és un projecte de jiwar- fundación al fanar- novact nova amb el suport de l'ajuntament de barcelona i l'accd per a recolzar les artistes àrabs en els seus contextos de creació.
dilluns 12 de novembre a les 19h a l’ @iemed_bcn c.girona,20. 
presentació en anglès amb traducció simultània al català.
#igersbarcelona #igerscatalunya #metoo #performance #theatre #storytelling #illustration #feminismo #feminism

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

with ficial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
igår var vi på en samarbetskonferens med polismyndigheten region nord, brottsofferjouren västernorrland samt länsstyrelsen västernorrland i frågor som berör brottsutsatta personer.

konferensens teman var demokratibrott, den nya sexualbrottslagstiftningen samt #metoo, hashtaggen som blivit till en revolution.

vi vill tacka alla för en riktigt bra dag! lars edlund (ordförande brottsofferjouren västernorrland), thomas nilsson (chef utredningsenheten polisregion nord), ylva aller (länsråd länsstyrelsen västernorrland), jeanette gustafsdotter (vd tidningsutgivarna), eva sund (kommissarie grundläggande rättigheter, polismyndigheten, nationella operativa avdelningen), louise lundqvist (jurist från brottsoffermyndigheten), olivia björklund dahlgren (vice ordförande fatta), elsa levinson (styrelseledamot i fatta) samt alexandra pascalidou!

#polisen #metoo #föreläsning #fatta #juridik #demokratibrott #revolution #konferens #sundsvall

text:
at a hearing before the senate judiciary committee, christopher wylie described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters. the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like ‘drain the swamp’ or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the ‘deep state’ that weren’t necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement.

jon sharman
the independent

text: caloriën verlaagd maar 2800 💀ja ik weet dat dat voor jou veel is... maar ik zit met mijn verbruik dan echt in een dik tekort. 📉veel mensen claimen ook altijd veel lager te zitten dan ze daadwerkelijk eten, vergeten dingen mee te rekenen. ze eten een klein hapje extra, een olie’tje waar je in bakt niet mee rekenen, 3 liter rivella light drinken waar dan toch 150 kcal in zit, 2 flessen light saus per dag voor 200 kcal. 🔍 dit zijn producten die misschien slim zijn om te gebruiken of weinig kcal leveren, maar alles bij elkaar telt het toch op. blijf precies! nog een tip om niet te laag te hoeven gaan in kcal tijdens je prep: begin op tijd! en begin op tijd het serieus te nemen. 🕑 veel atleten schrikken 6 weken voor hun wedstrijd dat het toch wel is echt dichtbij begint te komen, en gaan dan pas echt aan de slag. 🚀 misschien haal je het juiste vetpercentage nog, misschien niet, maar optimaal is het nooit... 🤓 #tipvandedag 🔬 #teammiro 🖤

text:
ett år efter skådespelaruppropet #tystnadtagning upplever de kvinnliga skådespelarna att branschen lyssnat. det sade moa gammel, en av dem som skrev på uppropet, på en presskonferens.
.
– branschen har verkligen lyssnat, och verkligen tagit oss på allvar. vi hade inte kunnat göra någonting utan en bransch som backar upp oss. under metoo pratade folk om en revolution – men utan stöd kommer vi att gå tillbaka till där vi var innan metoo, eller ännu längre tillbaka, sade moa gammel.
.
#tystnadtagning, uppropet som närmare 1000 kvinnliga skådespelare sedermera skrev under, blev startskottet för en hel rad metooupprop från många olika branscher och samhällsgrupper.

#metoo

text:
bom, manas, apesar de ainda termos muita luta pela frente, o feminismo vem crescendo cada vez mais e, junto com ele, diversos movimentos contra o assédio surgiram também! um dos melhores exemplos é o time’s up, que impactou hollywood fortemente após os escândalos envolvendo o produtor harvey weinstein. criado por natalie portman e meryl streep, entre outras artistas, time’s up é uma iniciativa que já arrecadou milhões para dar apoio legal a mulheres e homens que foram assediados sexualmente no local de trabalho. junto com o #metoo, o movimento abalou as estruturas hollywoodianas, incentivando diversas mulheres a denunciarem seus agressores, dos quais muitos eram grandes nomes famosos. uma outra inciativa maravilhosa, dessa vez criada aqui no brasil, foi o manifesto “deixa ela trabalhar”. o movimento, que envolve 52 jornalistas de esporte, luta contra o assédio sofrido pelas profissionais nos estádios, ruas e redações. são esses protestos que nos dão esperança e mostram como nós, mulheres, merecemos respeito e dignidade no ambiente de trabalho. jamais iremos nos calar! juntas somos mais fortes! 
#mulheres #mulheresreais #woman #women #feminist #assedio #metoo #timesup #deixaelatrabalhar

text_retweet:
being in a relationship with a narcissist had you up and down, confused, concerned, wanting out but staying in...the whole thing is such a circus, it’s unreal. *
*
and if they had another affliction like an addiction of some kind (which most do), it became your entire world. *
*
this is why we say no-contact. it’s imperative. if you do have to have contact there are things you do to keep him as disinterested in you as possible: *
*
1) be boring: this means one word answers or a simple sentence, no emotion, and stick to the topic (don’t let them pull you into anything). *
*
2) you have to have the understanding that anything you say will be used against you and nothing you say will make one bit of difference. do you get that? there’s no point. you’re not going to “reach him” because that part of him doesn’t exist: there’s zero logic or reasoning. it will never happen. *
*
he wants to make you crazy, so if you want it to stop, you have to start conditioning him that he can’t come to you for his fix. *
*
your emotional state gets him high: he needs that, so don’t give it to him ever again.*
*
____________
#repost @narcissist_survivor ♥️

do you want to secure our borders? do you think it is crazy that sweden, germany, and other european countries have imported thousands of rapists from africa and the middle east? do you think that your country should prefer citizens to foreigners, workers to parasites, decent people to criminals? only nazis would think that way! you don’t want to be a nazi, do you? then stop protesting against policies that will destroy white people. after all, the only way for white people to atone for the crimes of nazis is by ceasing to exist.

this kind of rhetoric is so asinine, and the aims it advances are so evil, that it should be child’s play to demolish it. but we have had more than 90 years of anti-nazi propaganda dinned into us by now, which has created a powerful moral inhibition to think rationally about any policies, no matter how sensible, if they are stigmatized as “just like the nazis.” to make matters worse, there are plenty of our own people who happily collaborate in this process of stigmatizing and marginalizing sensible policies as “nazi.” https://www.counter-currents.com/2016/04/why-ramzpaul-is-right/
